title: virginia style crab cakes
directions: Combine crab meat, baking powder, mustard and Old Bay seafood seasoning together.
Mix egg and bread crumbs together.
Now combine other ingredients.
Mix all ingredients well together. Then form cakes; fry in Wesson oil or favorite oil until golden brown.

title: stuffed pasta shells
directions: Boil package of jumbo shells until tender.
Drain.
Cool for about 5 minutes.
In a bowl, mix all 3 cheeses together.
Take pasta shells and stuff the cheese into individual pasta shells. (Set shells aside.)
Brown meat in a skillet.
Don't forget to use your Pam!
Drain.
Now, mix meat and spaghetti sauce together and heat.
Add herbs, basil, oregano and garlic.
Set aside.
Place pasta shells on a baking sheet.
Place in oven at 350°.
Heat until cheeses are melted.
Take shells out.
Place 3 or 4 on a plate.
Take sauce mixture and pour over shells.
Serve with salad and bread.
Serves 6.

title: do nothing cake
directions: Combine all ingredients (except Topping) and mix by hand.
Do not use an electric mixer.
Pour into a greased 9 x 12-inch pan and bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Spread topping over cake while warm.
Makes 12 servings.

title: pineapple upside-down cake(serves 8)
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve liquid.
Half the slices.
Melt butter in 9 x 1 1/2-inch round baking pan.
Stir in brown sugar and 1 tablespoon pineapple liquid to make 2/3 up.
Arrange pineapple in pan.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar.
Mix all ingredients together with spoon.
May use all at one or keep half in refrigerator for use later.
Use only enough flour to handle well. Roll and cut biscuits.
Bake until brown.
12 minutes.
400°. Not necessary to let rise.
Place on a greased pan.
Brush with oil.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt together peanut butter, chocolate chips and margarine over low heat.
Let cool and pour over cereal.
Stir until coated. Put 3 cups powdered sugar in brown grocery bag.
Pour cereal in bag and shake.
Spread on paper towels.
Let dry 1 to 2 hours. Refrigerate or freeze.

title: bean dip
directions: Melt Velveeta cheese in a crock pot.
When melted add all other ingredients. Serve warm in crock pot.

title: dilly bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
In large bowl, combine the next 8 ingredients.
Add yeast to this mixture.
Add flour; mix well. Cover; let rise until double.
Stir down and turn into greased casserole dish.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Brush with butter; sprinkle with salt after you remove bread from pan.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: In skillet, in a tablespoon oil, stir-fry 1/2 of chicken until brown.
Remove and repeat with remaining chicken.
In 1 tablespoon oil, stir-fry vegetables with ginger and garlic powder until just tender.
Add soup, soy sauce and vinegar.
Heat to boil.
Return chicken to skillet.
Serve over rice.

title: quick enchilada casserole
directions: Place frozen enchiladas in glass baking dish; pour chili undiluted over enchiladas.
Spread out evenly.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Spread cheese over top and return to oven until cheese is melted.
Serves 6.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Mix meal and sugar.
Stir in sour cream and eggs.
Blend well and stir in vegetable oil.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix onion soup mix, mushroom soup and 1 can water.
Add uncooked rice.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place uncooked chicken seasoned with Creole seasoning.
Cover with aluminum foil and cook at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: three cheese lasagne roll-ups
directions: Cook lasagne according to package directions.
Combine three cheeses with eggs, spinach, pepper and nutmeg.
Spread thin layer of sauce in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread cheese mixture evenly on lasagne.
Roll up and place seam side down in dish. Repeat.
Cover with remaining sauce.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 25 minutes, then, uncovered, for 5 minutes longer.

title: old-timey single pie crust(double for cobblers or two crust pies)
directions: Mix well and chill.
Roll out for use in pies, cobblers, etc.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together thoroughly.
Sift next 2 ingredients together and stir in.
Mix in chopped nuts.
Chill dough about 30 minutes.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix well.
Store in closed container.
Use 3 teaspoons per cup of boiling water.

title: spinach artichoke dip
directions: Mix cheese, mayonnaise, chilies, spinach and artichokes.
Pour into lightly buttered flat pan or pie dish.
Place under broiler for several minutes, until heated through and top is browned. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine oats and sour cream.
Stir in melted margarine, eggs and brown sugar; mix well.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Stir into oat mixture.
Divide into 2 (12-cup) muffin pans.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pecan kisses
directions: Beat
egg
white
until stiff.
Add brown sugar.
Blend well. Preheat
oven
Spoon onto well-greased cookie sheet (about 3/4 teaspoon each time).
Add a pecan half on top of each. Bake for
minutes
and turn oven off, leaving in oven for 30 more minutes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix well and pour into 1 pound coffee can.
Put can in 3 pound coffee can and cover.
Pour ice and rock salt around 1 pound can until 1/2 full.
Roll fast for 15 minutes.
Drain off ice.
Add more if necessary.
Roll for at least another 15 minutes.

title: chicken chablis
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Melt butter in large skillet.
Cook chicken until lightly brown, about 4 minutes on each side.
Remove chicken from pan and set aside.
Add apple juice or Chablis and jelly to pan drippings.
Simmer until jelly is melted. Stir constantly.
Return chicken to pan and baste with sauce. Cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.

title: marshmallow popcorn ball
directions: Melt margarine.
Add marshmallows and stir until melted.
Add gelatin if desired.
Pour over popped corn.
Form into balls.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients together.
To the orange juice, add butter and enough boiling water to make 3/4 cup.
Then slowly add to dry ingredients.
Add egg and mix well.
Fold in cranberries. Pour into greased and floured loaf pan and bake in 325° oven for 1 hour.
Test for doneness by inserting cake tester into center. Cool at least 10 minutes and remove from pan and cool on rack.

title: italian style shells 'n cheese
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat Velveeta Italiana and milk in medium saucepan on medium heat until Velveeta is melted, stirring occasionally.
Stir in beans, shells, tomato and seasoning.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mexican hominy
directions: Saute the onion in oleo.
Mix all ingredients and put in a 9 x 9-inch casserole dish. Cover with chips and cook at 350° until it bubbles, about 30 minutes.

title: meatballs
directions: Crumble up slice of bread.
Add to it the beef, milk, oregano and onion salt.
Form into balls.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, mix cream of chicken soup and water. Brown meatballs in skillet, then add meatballs to soup mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Makes 16 meatballs.

title: pizza popcorn
directions: Melt butter; stir in other ingredients except cheese.
Pour over popcorn.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over popcorn and toss lightly until coated.

title: seaside pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta without salt and drain and cool.
Toss shredded crab, pepper, onion and parsley together and set aside.
Combine soy sauce, oil, vinegar and sugar, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Pour soy sauce mixture over crab mixture.
Gently toss together.
Chill 2 to 4 hours to allow flavors to blend.
Toss again just before serving.

title: pineapple muffins
directions: Drain pineapple liquid into a measuring cup.
Add enough milk to make 1 cup.
Combine with egg and orange rind.
In separate bowl, sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and nutmeg. Blend milk mixture into dry ingredients along with the melted butter, mixing just until batter is blended.
Stir in crushed pineapple.

title: pizza loaf
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and form a loaf.
Top with sauce, onion and olives. Cook in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until cooked through.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook
squash
and
onion,
drain.
Add butter, salt and pepper,
and milk.	Mix together, then add beaten eggs, cheese and cracker crumbs.
Put in casserole.	Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cole slaw superb
directions: Cut cabbage in half.
Then half again to make wedges.
Cut on the diagonal into thin strips.
Mix with onion and carrots. Combine green pepper with salt, sugar, vinegar and mayonnaise. Toss with slaw and refrigerate at least one hour

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach and rice according to directions.
Combine all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Place all ingredients except poppy seed in large mixer bowl. Stir until well blended.
Add poppy seed.
Pour into well-greased angel food pan.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Place butter in 1-quart measuring cup.
Microwave at High 1/2 minute.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Gradually stir in milk and microwave on High 8 to 10 minutes, stirring well after 4 to 5 minutes.

title: cornmeal sugar cookies
directions: Beat margarine and brown sugar until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat.
Mix flour, cornmeal, baking powder and salt.
Add to sugar mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Shape into three 12-inch rolls. Chill.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven about 8 minutes, or until brown.
Cool on rack.

title: fish fillets
directions: Cut fish into 4 to 6 portions, and put into shallow buttered casserole dish. Mix the next 6 ingredients and pour over fish. Let stand until fish is thawed. When ready to bake, top each piece of fish with 1 onion slice and 1 tomato slice. Sprinkle over top, a mixture of corn flake crumbs and parmesan cheese. Dot with butter. Bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes, or until top is a golden brown. Serve with sauce from pan.

title: calico bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except bacon.
Place in baking dish. Crumble bacon on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: corned beef jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add pinch of salt.
Chill until it begins to jell.
After jello begins to jell fold in corned beef, cucumber, green pepper, onion, celery and eggs.
Last, fold in mayonnaise.
Put in ring mold until firm.

title: funnel cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spoon batter into a funnel, closing the bottom with your finger until ready to drop into hot shortening, which is placed into ordinary skillet (3/4 full of melted shortening).
Brown both sides and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: whole wheat muffins
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine first 6 ingredients.
In another small bowl, beat yogurt, eggs and oil together.
In the large mixing bowl, make a well (dig a small hole in the middle of the mixed dry ingredients).
Pour the liquid ingredients all at once into the well you made in the large bowl.
Mix gently just until the flour mixture is moistened.
Pour into 12 greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° until brown, about 18 to 20 minutes.

title: red tomato salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients except crushed tomatoes in a large bowl; mix well.
Place about 3/4 mixture in a food processor, fitted with steel blade, and process for about 5 seconds.
Return to bowl with remaining salsa mixture.
Add crushed tomatoes and mix well.
Cover tightly and allow to chill at least 1 hour before serving.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: brown rice casserole
directions: Put rice in baking dish.
Pour consomme on top of rice.
Pour mushroom soup into dish and stir in.
Cut margarine into small pieces and place in casserole.
Sprinkle in chopped onion.
Stir if necessary to saturate ingredients.

title: salsa
directions: Cook all ingredients together until desired thickness.
Add onions the last 1/2 hour.
Can.

title: baked beans
directions: The night before, wash beans and cover with water.
(Do not use as much water as you would if you were making beans and rice. Just barely cover the beans with water.)
The next morning, put beans on to cook, about 1/2 hour.
Later, in a small amount of oil, saute vegetables until clear.
Add the can of tomato sauce to vegetables and stir.
Add to beans and cook until beans are tender.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350 degrees for 1-1/2 hours.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix together in a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan flour, baking soda, sugar and salt.
Make 3 holes.
In first hole put in vanilla, second hole put in vinegar and third hole put in oil.
Pour water over all.
Mix well with fork.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. This cake is very dark and it is extremely moist.

title: company wilted cabbage
directions: In a large skillet, brown bacon until crisp.
Drain off fat and wrap bacon in paper towel.
Set aside.
Saute onion in butter or bacon fat.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper to taste.
Add 2 tablespoons water.
Shred the cabbage and add 2 tablespoons vinegar; add to the rest of ingredients in skillet except bacon. Steam all until cabbage is tender.

title: ruby's favorite pound cake
directions: Bring eggs, Crisco, margarine and milk to room temperature. Cream
together sugar, Crisco and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift
flour
and baking powder together.
Add flour alternately
with milk and beat well after each addition.
(Do not omit beating together after each addition; this makes the cake fluffy).
Add flavorings.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Put
in
cold oven (do not preheat).	Bake at 350° for
1 hour
or
until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool before removing from pan.

title: fresh shrimp
directions: Place water, vegetables and seasonings in saucepan.
Heat to simmering point.
Wash shrimp, drop in broth and allow to simmer 12 to 15 minutes.
Permit to cool.
Remove shrimp, shell and take out back vein of each shrimp.
Shrimp may now be chilled for salads, cocktails, etc. or dipped in batter to be French fried.

title: cheese strata
directions: Make 1 layer of bread on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add a layer of cheese and another layer of bread. Top with layer of cheese.
Combine eggs, milk, minced onion, salt and dry mustard. Pour over cheese and bread and refrigerate at least 6 hours or overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 55 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together.
Roll into balls and press with fork; place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: tex-mex salad
directions: Spread bean dip in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix avocados, lemon juice, salt and pepper and spread over bean dip.
Next, mix sour cream, Miracle Whip and taco seasoning and spread over avocado mixture.
Sprinkle with onions, tomatoes and olives. Cover with grated cheese.
Serve with chips.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Warm olive oil in 8-quart pressure cooker.
Combine sausage and ground round and brown in olive oil.
Stir until no red or pink is visible in meat.
Add onions and garlic and continue to stir.
Add tomato sauce and crushed tomatoes.
Add all spices and stir well.
Add mushrooms with juice.
Add wine.
Continue to stir until sauce begins to boil.
Put pressure cooker lid on and bring up to pressure.
Reduce heat and cook for 45 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand for 10 minutes.
Open pressure cooker and serve sauce over cooked spaghetti.
Will freeze well.
Great for one of those days when you get home late and don't know what to fix for dinner.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients for sauce.
Lay chicken pieces in pan, skin side up.
Baste with sauce.
Cook at 325° for 1 1/2 hours, basting often as chicken cooks.
This sauce will do for about 3 1/2 pounds of chicken.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Heat in oil for 5 minutes with onions.
Add soup.
Heat until bubbles.
Reduce heat.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into baking dish.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add eggs and salad oil. Just stir.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple and bananas.
Divide into 3 well-greased and floured pans.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: marshmallow brownies
directions: Cream the oleo and sugar well.
Add eggs and blend.
Sift flour, salt and cocoa. Gradually add to first mixture. Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Remove from oven and cover at once with marshmallows.

title: bacon and cheese cornbread
directions: Preheat and grease a medium cast-iron skillet.
Heat corn meal and milk over medium heat until thick and dry.
Stir frequently for 3 minutes, then spoon into mixing bowl.
Add butter and eggs and beat until smooth.
Stir in salt, baking powder, cheese and bacon.
Pour into preheated cast-iron skillet (or baking pan). Bake at 325° for 35 minutes or until cooked through.
Serves 4.

title: cinnamon buns
directions: Mix yeast, milk, potatoes, margarine and sugar.
Add flour. Mix well and let stand 20 minutes.
Add eggs, salt and 11 to 12 cups flour. Knead really well.
Let rise until double.
Punch down and roll out for buns.
Spread on butter, brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Makes approximately 13 pans.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook and drain spinach very well. Let cool. Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate for 1/2 to 1 hour.
Roll into balls.
Freeze.
Before serving, place on cookie sheet still frozen.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: crock-pot lemon roast chicken
directions: Wash chicken; pat dry. Season chicken with salt and pepper. Sprinkle half the oregano and garlic on chicken. Melt butter in large frying pan. Brown chicken on all sides. Transfer to crock-pot. Sprinkle with remaining oregano and garlic. Add sherry or water to frying pan. Stir to loosen brown bits. Pour into crock-pot. Cover. Cook on low for 8 hours. Add lemon juice the last 1/2 hour of cooking.

title: banana pudding
directions: Cook in top of double boiler, stirring constantly, until custard sets or thickens.
Cool.
Slice 3 medium bananas into custard.
Line bottom and sides of baking dish with vanilla wafers.
Alternate layers of custard mix and vanilla wafers.
Top with meringue.

title: easy rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.

You may either place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and bake for 30 minutes at 350°; or place in a medium saucepan and bring to a boil on top of the stove. Reduce heat and simmer covered 20 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.

title: peach pie
directions: Pour peaches and juice into large casserole dish.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and flour; mix well and spread over peaches (do not stir).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cashew cheese
directions: Blend all together in blender.
Pour into saucepan and simmer, stirring constantly, until thick.
Use hot or cold.

title: chocolate peanut crisps
directions: Mix peanut butter, powdered sugar and milk.
Mix well and spread between crackers.
Melt chocolate chips and vegetable shortening.
Dip crackers in chocolate.
Place on wax paper until firm.
Store in cool place or refrigerate.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: sour cream pound cake #2
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Beat with electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt cake pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted into cake comes out clean.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes and vegetables until tender.
Put in blender with salt and butter.
Thin soup to desired consistency with chicken stock.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley and paprika.

title: lemon no bake cheesecake
directions: In small bowl, dissolve gelatin with water; set aside.
Beat cream cheese, then add gelatin.
Fold in whipped topping and pour mixture into crust.
Chill 4 hours.
Serve with cherry pie filling or favorite flavor.

title: peanut butter play dough(this is great for little kids!)
directions: Mix ingredients together to get proper consistency for modeling.
Any leftover dough should be refrigerated.
This dough is edible.

title: mother's sugar cookies
directions: Fill a medium size mixing bowl 2/3 full flour. Make a hole in the middle of the flour, leaving some on the bottom. Put lard, salt, soda and baking powder in the flour. Add beaten eggs and milk. Mix well and roll out in balls; sprinkle with sugar and flatten with fork. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: green pea salad
directions: Drain liquid from peas; place in bowl.
Add diced onion to peas; chop 1 egg into mixture.
Add salad dressing until ingredients are covered and creamy.
Slice remaining egg over top; sprinkle with paprika.
Chill for at least 1 hour before serving. Serve on lettuce as a salad or as a vegetable side dish with your meal.

title: carrot salad
directions: Peel, slice thick and boil veggies until tender.
Cut pepper and onion to your choice of thickness.
Mix all other ingredients. Cover veggies and marinate in refrigerator overnight or at least 12 hours.

title: chicken cordon bleu calzones
directions: Place chicken in a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Cover with water. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done. In a skillet, saut mushrooms and onions in margarine until tender. Combine cornstarch and milk until smooth; stir into skillet.
Add seasonings and bring to a boil.

Cook and stir until thickened. Drain chicken. Cut pastry shells in half lengthwise. On one side of each half, place a chicken breast, 1/4 cup mushroom mixture, 2 ham slices and 1 cheese slice. Fold pastry over filling and seal edges.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Brush tops with milk. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until puffed and golden.
Yields 4 servings.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger, bread crumbs, salt, pepper, eggs and onions. Make into small balls. Brown in skillet.
Mix barbecue sauce and preserves. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or put in slow cooker and let simmer.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Defrost soup partially.
Mix together with cream cheese.
Use mixer or by hand.
Dice shrimp into small pieces.
Remove 1/2 dozen and save.
Add remaining shrimp to soup and cream mixture; add remaining ingredients.
Cut top of bread, about 1/2 inch. Tear out bite-size pieces from center of bread.
Put dip in center and garnish with remaining shrimp.
Serve on tray with small pieces of bread surrounding it.
Yields 10 to 15 people.

title: cornbread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients. Beat eggs. Add milk and oil and add to dry mixture. Fill greased pan half full. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil and zucchini.
In a separate bowl, mix flour, salt, cinnamon, soda and baking powder.
Beat egg until foamy. Add vanilla and sugar mixture.
Add flour mixture to egg.
Blend. Add nuts.
Divide batter into two greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at about 350° for 1 hour, until done.
Cool on rack.

title: mexican soup
directions: Crumble and brown ground meat.
Put in colander and wash off. Put meat back in pot.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat and serve.
Freezes great!

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and eggs, adding one at a time; beat well.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk; add to cream mixture. Place dates, nuts, orange slices and coconut in large bowl; coat with flour.
Mix all together by hand.
Dough will be stiff.
Flour and grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 or 3 hours.

title: cocoa apple cake
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar, margarine and water until fluffy. Sift together flour, cocoa, baking soda, cinnamon and allspice. Add to cream mixture and mix well.
Fold in nuts, chocolate morsels, apples and vanilla until evenly distributed.
Spoon into greased and floured 10-inch loose tube pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 60 to 70 minutes until done.
Yield:
about 10 servings.

title: dilly casserole bread
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Combine rest of ingredients in bowl. Add flour to form stiff dough.
Cover; let rise (85° to 90°) until double, 50 to 60 minutes.
Stir down.
Turn into greased 8-inch round casserole (1 1/2 to 2-quart).
Let rise 30 to 40 minutes. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Brush with soft butter and sprinkle with salt.

title: bow tie salad
directions: Cook bow tie macaroni until firm.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Melt cheese with soup over medium heat.
Combine pepper, onion and mayonnaise.
Add noodles and sauce.
Mix thoroughly and bake in oven 45 minutes at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Divide bread crumbs into 3 halves.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix 1/2 bread crumbs in skillet with butter.
Saute onion, peppers, 1/2 more bread crumbs, squash, eggs, salt, milk, sugar and black pepper.
Pour in buttered dish.
Sprinkle with rest of bread crumbs.
Bake 1 hour.
Remove from heat.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Put rice in a buttered casserole.
Top with chicken pieces. Mix soups with water and pour over chicken and rice.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 300°.

title: spiced cranberry cider
directions: Combine all ingredients in large kettle.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
With slotted spoon, remove cinnamon, cloves and lemon slices.
If desired, float fresh lemon slices in each cup.

title: tortellini primavera
directions: Cook the pasta according to directions and drain.
Slice and saute the zucchini, squash and onion in the oil.
Add sliced tomatoes, garlic, pepper and oregano.
Cook until tender.
Serve over the pasta.
Serves four.

title: diet thousand island dressing
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Blend into yogurt.
Chill for at least 1 hour before using (overnight is best).
Yield:
1 1/2 cups. Contains 11 calories per tablespoon.

title: chicken pie
directions: Take cooked chicken off the bone.
Put into bottom of casserole dish.
Cover with cream of celery soup and chicken broth.
Mix margarine, flour, pepper, salt, baking powder and milk; pour over chicken and soup mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes at 425°.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour until it is the size of small peas. Add water and stir into ball.
Divide into 3 portions.
Roll out on lightly floured board.
Makes three 9-inch pie crusts.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in bowl and set aside.
In a separate bowl, beat eggs until fluffy and then add melted butter and milk. Fold in dry ingredient mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch greased pan or lined muffin tray.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mama's fried pork spareribs and gravy
directions: Slice into portions of 2 or three rib sections.
Season with salt and pepper to your desire.
Put three cups of all purpose flour into a bag.
Add ribs and shake to coat.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: I sometimes add a few shakes of Tabasco sauce.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt. Cut in shortening with pastry blender or fork.
Add cheese and milk.
Stir to mix.

title: barb's quick scalloped potatoes
directions: Rinse off ham hocks and place in a large pot (5-quart size). Cook ham hocks until tender.
Add the green beans and add more water, if necessary.
Add the salt, pepper and bacon drippings. Continue to cook until the beans are tender.

title: white bean chili
directions: Cover beans in 3 inches of cold water and soak overnight.

title: tuna-stuffed eggs
directions: Split boiled eggs in half.
Remove yolks; set aside halves.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichoke hearts and save liquid.
Place all ingredients in food processor or blender.
Process until smooth.
Add liquid from artichoke hearts until desired consistency is reached.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serve with breadsticks or French bread, or put into mushroom caps and brush with melted butter.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: gobblers for gobbling "turkey treats"
directions: Carefully separate each cookie, leaving cream filling on one side (a blunt knife helps, and children love to help make broken pieces disappear!).
Set cookie halves without filling aside.

title: bacon and egg casserole
directions: Layer all ingredients in a 2-quart or 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
This may be made the night before and refrigerated overnight.
Bake as directed.

title: shoyu chicken
directions: Bring
to
boil
all ingredients, except
chicken.
Add chicken to sauce mixture; simmer for 40 minutes.
Turn chicken over to brown evenly.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: In 9 x 13-inch baking pan, spread pie filling.
In large bowl, cream butter.
Add dry cake mix to butter; blend well.
Spoon mixture over pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: meatballs for 50
directions: Grind meat 3 times.
Add bread crumbs (that were soaked in the cream).
Add soda water and egg yolks.
Shape into small balls.

title: turtle pie
directions: Melt caramel over low heat, stirring frequently to avoid burning.
After caramel is melted, stir in 1/4 cup cream until blended.
Stir in 2 cups pecan pieces.
Pour into crust and spread evenly.

title: lil smokies
directions: Place little smokies in a slow cooker.
Pour barbecue sauce on top.
Stir frequently and cook on low until hot.
I use 3 or 4 packages of little smokies to each bottle of barbecue sauce.

title: mayonnaise dressing
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt and dry mustard.
Add egg and beat together.
Then take 1/2 cup vinegar and finish filling the cup with water.
Beat until smooth.
Add butter and cook in a double boiler.

title: grandma cole's thanksgiving jello
directions: Mix jello, using juice from pineapple as part of water called for.
Mix in fruit at this time, also.
Let set.
When set, fork jello apart.
Mix cottage cheese and Cool Whip in.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Steam peppers 5 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients, reserving 1/2 can of soup.
Mix well.
Fill peppers with stuffing mix.
Bake in shallow pan at 375° for 30 minutes.
Pour remaining soup over peppers.
Return to oven.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: wassail
directions: Heat to a low boil; put in crock-pot.
Serve warm.

title: chicken bake
directions: Place chicken pieces on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soups and milk and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle stuffing over mixture.
Pour broth over the top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: carrot bread
directions: Into flour put soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix together salad oil, eggs and sugar; add flour and then grated carrots.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool 15 minutes before dumping.
Fill pan 1/2 full.

title: calico bean bake
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and pour in baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sausage stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushroom caps.
Chop and set aside.
Cook sausage in skillet; drain, but reserve 2 tablespoons of drippings. Cook stems in drippings over medium heat until tender.
Remove from heat and add sausage, cheese and crumbs.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Fill caps with mixture and bake for 15 minutes.

title: gone-all-day stew
directions: Mix together soup, water or wine and flour until smooth. Combine with remaining ingredients in a covered roasting pan. Bake at 275° for 4 to 5 hours.
When ready to serve, adjust seasoning.
Serve over noodles or with crusty French bread.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Butter a 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Layer 1 layer of sliced potatoes, salt and pepper to taste, 1 teaspoon parsley, 1/3 of fried bacon, 1/2 tablespoon flour, 1 teaspoon butter (placed as 4 small dots) and diced onions (if desired).
Make 2 more layers. Heat up milk (at least enough so when poured over potatoes it comes to the top of them).
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours in oven or 20 to 30 minutes in microwave.
If using microwave, cover with wax paper.
May top with cheese.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and shape into a ball. Roll in the chopped nuts.
Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken dressing
directions: In large bowl mix bread, seasoning, onion and eggs; mix well. Add chicken; stir well.
Pour chicken broth over bread mixture. Let set a few minutes.
(Add more broth to moisten.)
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° until top is browned.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes and press between paper towels.
Press potatoes on the bottom of 9-inch pie pan, ungreased.
Drizzle butter over the potatoes.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
Combine cheese, ham and onions; spoon over the potatoes.
Beat together milk, eggs, salt and pepper; pour over the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Allow to set 10 minutes before serving.

title: lite vegetable pie
directions: Combine egg, mayonnaise, seasoning, onions and pepper; stir in bread crumbs and tuna (undrained).
Put this in a pie plate; take a spoon and shape the mixture to fit like a pie shell.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients; press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: beer batter for fish, zucchini or onion rings
directions: Whip ingredients, cover and refrigerate for 1 day.
Heat deep oil to very hot.
Dip fillets or vegetables in batter.
Let drip, then fry, keeping oil moving.
Turn with slotted spoon.
Fry until medium brown.
Clear oil periodically of drips.
Drain on paper towel.
Keep in oven.

title: homemade spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in olive oil until tender.
Brown meat; drain.
In large saucepan, combine onion mixture, meat, and remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, stirring frequently. Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for approximately 1 hour.
Uncover and simmer for another hour or longer.
The longer it cooks the tastier it gets.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add vanilla and almond extract and blend well.
Add eggs, one at a time, and continue beating after each addition.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture and milk alternately to creamed mixture and beat well.
Pour into large greased and floured tube pan or two loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done.

title: green beans with cashews(servings:  8)
directions: Cut ends off beans.
Cut beans in 2-inch pieces and place in a large saucepan with boiling salted water.
Cover and cook until tender, but still crisp, 7 to 10 minutes.
Drain; rinse under cold water to stop cooking.
May be refrigerated overnight.
Frozen green beans make this a quicker process without sacrificing taste. Before serving beans, melt butter or margarine in a large skillet.
Saute onion until tender.
Add green beans and cashews. Cook and stir until heated through.
Stir in lemon juice and parsley.
Season to taste with salt and white pepper.

title: killer bean dip
directions: Layer beans in bottom of lasagna pan.
Spread salsa over beans.
Mix the sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning together and spread as next layer.
Sprinkle cheese, then add onions, olives and tomatoes.
Heat for best results.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Make a loaf and roll in crushed crackers, parsley and chopped pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix together cream, flour, sugar, eggs and nutmeg.
Pour over peaches in pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake for 1/2 to 3/4 hour longer.
Cool.
Refrigerate.

title: no calorie russian tea
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
and store in empty Crystal Light can. Add
teaspoon	of
mix to 1 cup of boiling water to make a great cup of tea.

title: rosettes
directions: Beat eggs slightly with spoon.
Add vanilla, sugar, milk, flour, cornstarch and salt.
Mix.

title: leslie's lemon pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, sweetened condensed milk and lemonade together. Pour into pie crust.
Chill before serving.

title: icebox coconut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix cake using the eggs and water according to package directions.
Bake 30 minutes or until cake center springs back when pressed lightly.
Five minutes before cake is done, combine sugar and milk in saucepan and bring to a full boil.
Remove from heat and add flavoring.
Remove cake from oven.
Pierce with a fork at least 12 places.
Pour the hot mixture over cake.
Put in refrigerator until completely cool.
Spread Cool Whip over the top of the cake.
Press the coconut lightly into the Cool Whip.
Chill until ready to serve.
Keep tightly covered.

title: fruity chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken, grapes, apples and cabbage.
Pour lemon juice over mixture and stir.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and honey.
Add to chicken mixture and stir together.
Add nuts.
Stir. Especially good when salad is put in pita bread.

title: cheese-olive balls
directions: Mix ingredients in a medium bowl until crumbly.
Take about 1 teaspoon of mixture and roll in hands to warm dough.
Cover stuffed olives with dough and place on cookie sheet.
Preheat oven to 250° and cook balls until lightly browned.

title: salisbury steak with onion gravy
directions: In bowl combine 1/3 cup soup with ground beef, crumbs, egg, salt and pepper. Shape into 6 oval patties.
In frypan brown patties.
Drain off fat.
Gradually blend flour into remaining soup, mixing until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients, blending well.
Add to frypan.
Heat to boiling, stirring to loosen up brown bits.
Cover and cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add patties to gravy in frypan.
Cover and simmer an additional 15 minutes.
These patties freeze very well; place patties and gravy in a "freezer to oven" container for convenience.

title: easy stuffed eggs
directions: Slice eggs in half lengthwise and remove yolks.
Mash yolks; add sandwich spread, mayonnaise, salt and pepper, stirring until smooth.
Spoon or pipe into egg white halves.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: japanese fruitcake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients together and combine the two mixtures.
Flour the raisins and nutmeats and add to mixture.
Pour into layer pans and bake in slow oven at 300° for about 1 hour.

title: chocolate bread pudding
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in a double boiler top.
Cook over hot water until smooth.
Stir in butter.
Beat eggs until light and add salt, vanilla and milk.
Stir into chocolate mixture and cook until thick.
Pour into a serving dish.
(For a firmer pudding, pour into a buttered baking dish and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.) Serve hot or cold with whipped cream.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: barbecued chicken wings
directions: Wash and cut tips from chicken wings. Discard the wing tips. Cut wings into two pieces. Spread wings pieces in large shallow pan. Combine all ingredients above, stir well. Pour mixture over chicken. Bake at 350 degrees in oven about 1 hour or until sauce is absorbed, turn wings frequently. Serve hot.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Put chicken pieces in shallow baking dish.
Mix dressing, soup mix and preserves with a small amount of water.
Pour over chicken and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Serve over rice.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and remove stems.
Saute onion, oregano, garlic powder and parsley flakes until onion is tender.
Mix in softened cream cheese, Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs.
Fill mushroom caps; arrange on ungreased cookie sheet and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 15 minutes or until brown.
Serve warm.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger with one cut up onion.
Then put in crock-pot on low.
Add cans of diced green chillies, cans of soup and tortillas or corn chips.
Heat 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Just before serving, add the sour cream.

title: mock chicken
directions: Cook ground beef in skillet until brown; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients and mix well.
Place in 2-quart or larger casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown around the edges and not soft in the middle.

title: caramel corn (nonsticky)
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Cook and stir over medium heat until it bubbles around the edges.
Cook 5 minutes more.
Take off heat; stir in baking soda until foamy.
Pour over popped popcorn and stir.
Put into a 250° oven and bake for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: cocoa cake
directions: Cream together butter or margarine and sugar until smooth. Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat 1 minute at medium.
Sift the flour, cocoa and baking soda (salt, if needed).
Alternate with wet mixture until all mixed.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook whole chicken in crock-pot; debone when done.
Or use chicken breasts to obtain the amount of chicken you think you might need.
Save all of the chicken broth.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream together 3 cups powdered sugar, butter and flavoring until fluffy.
Add egg yolks and beat after each.
Stir together flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Add flour mixture and milk alternately to creamed mixture, beating well after each addition.
Stir in walnuts.

title: lasagna
directions: Boil noodles as directed on package and cool.
Brown meat and add seasoning and garlic.
Add sauce.
Mix the 3 cheeses in a bowl.
Layer in a lasagna pan the noodles, cheese mixture and meat sauce.
Makes 3 layers.
Sprinkle top with parsley and extra garlic.
Cook in preheated oven for 50 minutes at 375°.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: mama's ritz pie
directions: Beat egg whites.
Slowly add a scant cup of sugar and the vanilla.
Crush 23 Ritz crackers and add to egg whites.
Add one cup of chopped pecans.
Place in a well-greased 9-inch pie plate. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool thoroughly.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Place in a long dish.
Chill before serving.

title: strawberry pop cake
directions: Cook cake mix as directed.
(It's better if you use 1 small pan and 1 long pan.)
Cool.
Punch holes in top with fork.

title: bacon slaw
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Crumble and reserve 2 tablespoons drippings.
Combine drippings with vinegar, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Toss cabbage with onion, bell pepper and dressing.
Mix well, add bacon just before serving.
Serves 6.

title: steak for a king
directions: Pound flour into steak.
Brown in hot shortening.
Place in a large casserole.
Season with salt and pepper.
Layer sliced onions over meat.
Mix soups and milk.
Pour over meat and onion layers.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for at least 1 hour (until hot and bubbly).

title: lemon cake pudding
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Stir in rind, juice, yolks and milk.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into 1 quart casserole.
Set in a pan of water 1-inch deep.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 50 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: party dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, soup, dill weed and onion (do not use blender).
Add minced beef and chives.
Let stand in refrigerator. Serve on Club (or any) crackers.

title: perfected rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup of warm water.
In large mixing bowl with dough hook, beat together shortening, 2 cups water, salt, sugar and 6 cups of flour until not so lumpy.
Add yeast, water and beat in 3 to 3 1/2 more cups of flour.
Mix well.
Cover dough with damp cloth and let rise for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until doubled in bulk.
Turn out on floured board and roll about 1/2 inch thick. Cut or shape as desired.
Melted margarine may be put on the rolls.
Let rise second time for 1 to 2 hours or until doubled. Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk and cheese until soft dough forms.
Beat hard for 30 seconds.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto ungreased cooking sheet.
Bake in 450° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: crab meat fondue
directions: Melt butter and cream cheese in a double boiler.
Add crabmeat.
Place in fondue dish.
Keep warm.

title: cauliflower dip
directions: Mix the first four ingredients well and add mayonnaise.

title: corn puddin'
directions: Heat oleo and milk together.
Beat eggs good, adding to corn and cornstarch, then mix altogether.
Bake at 350° for about 45 to 50 minutes uncovered.

title: never fail banana bread
directions: Mix together all at once.
Bake in a greased loaf pan at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: corned beef hot dish
directions: Cook egg noodles until tender.
Mince onion and mix with chopped corned beef.
Mix in cheese, soup and milk and place in casserole.
Use crushed corn flakes to top.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add small amount of milk to hold together.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening and blend in milk.
Gather dough into a ball and knead only to hold together.
Roll or flatten on a floured surface.
Cut out biscuits and bake on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 12 minutes.

title: french toast
directions: Beat (mix) all together; dip 1/2 slice bread, at a time and fry in skillet.

title: hello dollies
directions: Spread softened butter on bottom of 9 x 9-inch baking pan. Then spread cracker crumbs over buttered pan.
Layer coconut, chocolate chips and pecans.
Pour condensed milk over layered mixture.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares or bars.

title: coconut shortbread
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar.
Add dry ingredients and coconut.
Make into a roll.
Chill very well.
Slice.
Bake at 350° until light brown.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Blend flour into Crisco and sugar with pastry blender. Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add soda to milk.
Add liquid to flour mixture.

title: barbecue beans(crock-pot)
directions: Drain and rinse beans, except pork and beans.
Mix all ingredients together in crock-pot.
Cook 4 hours (or more) on low.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Combine all ingredients in a large baking dish.
Put croutons on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quickie pizzas
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix all ingredients well.
Spread mixture on thin bread or English muffins. Place on cookie sheet.
Place in a 400° to 450° oven for 10 to 15 minutes until bottom of bread is toasty brown.
Can be topped with salami, smokie sausage, crisp bacon or mushrooms.
(Keeps well in refrigerator.)

title: low-fat applesauce bread
directions: Bring all ingredients to room temperature.
Put all ingredients into the bread machine in the order listed.
Select white bread and push "Start".

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full rolling boil.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add chips and peanut butter.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into 11 x 14-inch buttered pan. Chill and cut in pieces.

title: cinnamon bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Coat biscuit quarters in melted butter.
Combine cinnamon and sugars.
Drop biscuit in to coat. Place in a pan and sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 325°.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Combine cereal, sugar and water.
Let set one hour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix until moist.
Bake in nonstick pan or use muffin papers at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Potatoes may be boiled in their jackets, cooled, peeled and diced.
Or, if you are in a hurry, peel, cut into small pieces, boil, drain, mash, etc.
Shell eggs and discard half yolks (this cuts down on the cholesterol).
Chop pickles in food processor; mix all ingredients.
Season according to taste.
One teaspoon sugar makes everything taste better, and 1 teaspoon sugar is only 18 calories and contains no chemicals.

title: spinach and sprout salad
directions: Toss first 6 ingredients together.
Combine remaining ingredients, heat and simmer.
Pour over salad and toss. Serves 8.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheese come to room temperature for easier mixing.
Blend well, then add pecans, parsley and garlic.
Roll in another ounce or so of ground pecans.
Allow to stand at least 24 hours before serving.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Cut pound cake into 1-inch squares.
Mix pudding by package directions, omitting chilling.
Drain strawberries.
Mix strawberries with all but 1/3 cup Cool Whip.
Divide cake, pudding and strawberry Cool Whip mixture into thirds.
Layer in clear bowl in order (cake, pudding, Cool Whip mixture).
Reserve plain Cool Whip to spread on top.
Sprinkle with sliced almonds, if desired.
Chill and serve.

title: dole golden sauce(ready in 5 minutes)
directions: In saucepan, combine reserved juice and remaining ingredients. Heat until boils and thickens.
Add pineapple slices.
Heat through.
Spoon over Armour 1877 Ham.
Serves 5.

title: molasses cake
directions: Mix well.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli; drain and arrange in a 9 x 13-inch oblong pan. Put chicken on top.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice in bowl. Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle cheese on top.

title: curried fruit
directions: Arrange drained fruit in a large shallow baking dish.
In saucepan, bring remaining ingredients to a boil.
Pour over fruit and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: broccoli boats
directions: Brown ground chuck.
Heat chopped broccoli according to package directions.
Melt Velveeta cheese.
Combine meat, broccoli and cheese.
Then cut pistolettes in half.
Spoon mixture on pistolettes.
Bake at 350° until pistolettes brown and cheese bubbles.
Serve with chips and beverage of choice.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Combine all ingredients at once and mix well. Pour in 9
x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until done.

title: cinnamon twist
directions: This is a great recipe to make with kids.
It is so simple they can do it themselves, and it tastes good, too!

title: beer cheese soup
directions: In a heavy pan, melt butter and flour.
Mix until completely blended.
Heat over low flame for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add chicken broth and cream.
Mix until smooth and thick.
Add cheese and mix until all cheese is melted and soup is smooth.
Add beer and Worcestershire sauce and mix.
Mix in color and chives.
Simmer about 15 minutes, stirring constantly.
Serve piping hot with popcorn if desired.

title: "those little cheese potatoes"
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Prepare a 9 x 13-inch baking pan by spraying with Pam, then pat the potato mixture into it.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour or until bubbly. Remove from oven and let stand for 5 minutes.
Serve.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into graham cracker crust. Chill for one hour and top with chocolate curls.

title: mandarin delight
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Spread
in
a
x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool crust for 15 minutes.

title: pineapple cubes
directions: Arrange pineapple in sherbet glasses or small bowls.
Pour over chilled orange juice and serve garnished with a sprig of mint.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook
spaghetti;
stir in butter, egg and Parmesan.
In buttered pie plate, form spaghetti mixture into a crust shape. Add Ricotta,	then
sausage.	Cover
with
sauce.
Top
with Mozzarella cheese.	Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Brown beef in Dutch oven; do not drain fat.
Chop onions (large chunks), slice carrots, shred cabbage, slice celery and dice potatoes.
Add all ingredients to beef mixture.
Cook, covered, for 1 hour.
Remove cover; cook 1 hour more.

title: carrot cake
directions: Blend eggs and sugar.
Add next 5 ingredients.
By hand, blend well.
Measure and sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add to first mixture.
Add vanilla and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 375° for 50 or 55 minutes or until cake springs back.

title: jiffy basic sweet dough
directions: Put warm water into mixing bowl.
Add yeast and sugar; stir until dissolved.
Add shortening, unbeaten eggs, salt and 2 cups flour.
Mix with electric beater.
Add 1 more cup flour; continue beating with beater.
Add the last 3 cups of flour; finish beating with spoon.
Set in warm place until double, then spoon onto a well floured board.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Stir cucumbers, onion and salt.
Let stand 2 hours.
Drain in colander (don't wash).
Then stir all ingredients in bowl.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Pack in plastic bags, tie and freeze.

title: cavatini
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and mushrooms in oil.
Add pepperoni and heat thoroughly.
Add spaghetti sauce; continue to cook on low.
While sauce is heating, cook pasta as per package instructions for about 8 minutes.
Drain pasta and pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Stir half of the Mozzarella cheese into the sauce.
Pour the sauce over the pasta and stir.
Sprinkle remaining Mozzarella cheese into the mixture and bake in a 350° oven for about 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese is melted and mixture is heated throughout.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease baking sheet with butter flavor Crisco.
Combine butter flavor Crisco, light brown sugar, egg, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until blended.
Combine oats, flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix into creamed mixture at low speed just until blended.
Stir in raisins and nuts.

title: chocolate nut-date balls
directions: Mix sugar and milk.
Add dates and pecans.
Let set in refrigerator until chilled thoroughly.
Soften paraffin in double boiler.
Add chocolate chips.
Stir until melted.
Dip balls in paraffin and chocolate mix.
Place on wax paper.
Delicious!

title: scalloped turnips
directions: Mix flour, salt and paprika.
Dredge thinly sliced turnips in mixture.
Place in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking pan in even layer. Top with sliced onions, then turnips and continue until all are layered.
Dot each layer with bits of butter.
Heat milk on stove until hot, not boiling.
Pour milk over turnips.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 1/2 hour, covered with aluminum foil.
Take off foil and bake 30 to 45 minutes more, until golden on top.

title: barbara benson's almond roca cookies
directions: Melt chocolate in top of double boiler over hot, but not boiling water.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Pour in pie shell and bake at 350°.

title: potato soup
directions: In a large saucepan, melt oleo over medium-high heat.
Saute celery and onion until tender.
Add potatoes and broth.
Cover and simmer until tender.
Puree mixture in blender.
Return to saucepan.
Stir in milk and seasonings.
Add the cheese and heat only until melted.

title: summer fruit salad
directions: In a small jar with tight lid, combine oil, honey and lemonade concentrate.
Shake well.
In a medium bowl, combine fruit.
Pour dressing over fruit.
Toss gently.
Cover. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: brownies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually.
Add vanilla and eggs and blend well.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt together.
Add to butter mixture; add nuts and blend.
Grease and flour 1 (9 x 13-inch) pan and 1 (7 x 11-inch) pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: gingersnap cookies
directions: Mix flour, soda, salt and spices.
Cream the shortening and sugar well. Add eggs and beat.
Add dry ingredients.
Add molasses; stir all well. Chill 1 hour.
Makes into 1-inch balls. Roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Please grease pans.

title: oatmeal choco-nut cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Add chocolate chips, Hershey bar, and nuts.
Roll into balls and place 2 inches apart on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 375 degrees for 6 minutes.
Makes about 115 cookies.
Recipe can be cut in half.

title: chicken or turkey divine
directions: Cook broccoli and drain. Place butter in 8 x 12-inch baking dish and let melt in oven. Put broccoli in dish. Top with layer of chicken or turkey. Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder. Pour over meat. Top with cheese and bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serves about 6.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Mix together graham cracker crumbs (save 1/2 cup crackers for topping), sugar and melted butter.
Press into 9 x 13-inch glass Pyrex dish.
Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add cream cheese and sugar and mix together.
Put mixture over crumbs and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
When cool, add blueberry pie filling.
Whip whipping cream and confectioners sugar; place over berries.
Top with 1/2 cup cracker crumbs.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in 9 x 12-inch glass baking pan.
Arrange pineapple rings on bottom of dish.
Put cherries in the center of each slice.
In bowl, mix eggs, cake mix and juice. Pour on top of pineapple.
Bake approximately 30 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Let set for 5 minutes.
Turn upside-down on large platter.

title: tuna in tomato juice
directions: Soak gelatine 5 minutes in cold water and dissolve in 1 cup tomato juice which has been brought to a boil.
Cool.
Add to the other cup of tomato juice, lemon juice, salt and grated onion. When mixture begins to thicken, add celery, green pepper, olives, pickles and tuna fish.
Pretty molded in individual molds.

title: creamy potatoes and peas
directions: Place unpeeled potato wedges in sauce pan with water, cook until tender. Cook peas. Meanwhile saute onion in butter until tender. Stir in flour, salt, and pepper. Add milk and bring to a boil, cooking until thickened. Add dill. Drain potatoes and peas. Place in serving bowl. Pour the sauce over potatoes and peas and stir to coat. Serve hot. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Add the flour to the margarine and butter and stir. Add the milk. Add the cheese. Stir on low heat until sauce thickens. Serve over fresh vegetables. Broccoli is a good choice.

title: good morning muffins
directions: Brown sausage, stirring to crumble; drain and reserve drippings.
Add enough butter to drippings to equal 1/4 cup, set aside.
Combine flour and next three ingredients in medium bowl.

title: corn souffle
directions: Combine all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: icebox rolls
directions: In small bowl, combine shortening, sugar and salt.
With wooden spoon, beat until smooth and creamy.
Add boiling water; stir until smooth.
Set aside to cool until lukewarm.
In large bowl, sprinkle yeast over 1/2 cup warm water (take temperature of water with thermometer); stir until dissolved.
Add shortening mixture to yeast along with eggs and mix well.
Add flour alternately with 1 cup water.
Beat until smooth.
Grease top of dough; cover bowl tightly with foil.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: grape salad
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Stir in lemon juice and sour cream.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add grapes and pecans.
Stir to mix well.
Chill.

title: great dumplings
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients and cut in the shortening. Stir in milk to moisten dough thoroughly. Drop by teaspoon into low boiling chicken broth. Cover pan tightly for 15 minutes. Makes enough for 6 servings.

title: a.1. sloppy joes
directions: Cook meat until browned and add other ingredients.
Simmer about 15 minutes.
Spoon on buns.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: golden potato rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; set aside.
In a saucepan, combine milk, shortening and potatoes; cook and stir over low heat just until shortening is melted.
Remove from heat and place in a large bowl with sugar, salt, 2 cups of flour and the yeast mixture.
Add eggs and mix well.
Cover loosely and allow to stand for 2 hours (the dough will be like a sponge).
Stir in enough of the remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out onto a floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic, about 6 minutes. Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about (1 hour).
Punch down and divide into thirds.
On a floured surface, roll each portion into a 12-inch circle.
Cut each circle into 12 pie shaped wedges.
Start at the wide end, roll up each wedge.
Place rolls point side down, 2-inches apart on a greased baking sheet.
Cover and let rise 30 minutes or until nearly doubled.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: mom's crabcakes
directions: Trim and cube the bread, mix with crabmeat.
Add all other items.
Mix well and refrigerate 1 hour or more.
Brown in skillet and cook 20 minutes until done.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Beat eggs. Add flour and water.
Beat until smooth.
Dissolve chicken base in boiling water. Drop by spoonfuls in a thin stream, stirring until separated (slowly).

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix everything except tomato sauce and water.
Form into a loaf in casserole dish greased with bacon grease.
Pour the tomato sauce over top of the loaf, add 1 can water.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven. Halfway through cooking, add 1 or 2 slices of bacon on top of loaf, if desired.

title: salad relish
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: dog biscuits
directions: Mix all together.
Make into a ball and pat out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut out and place on cookie sheet.

title: black raspberry mousse
directions: Beat egg yolks, sugar and Chambord together until they become thick and yellow.
In a separate bowl, beat the cream until stiff, then fold it into the egg yolks and blend completely.
Pour into dessert cups and place in freezer for one hour.
Serve directly from freezer.
Makes 2 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Pour sugar over apples, mix and let stand.
Let the apples juice.
Mix all dry ingredients.
Separate 2 eggs and beat whites until stiff.
Pour cooking oil, egg yolks with apples and mix. Add dry ingredients, egg whites, and pecans; mix well.
Pour in tube or bundt pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Let stand about 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: meat croquettes
directions: Melt fat; add flour and blend.
Add milk and cook until very thick, stirring constantly.
Add meat, onions, seasonings and parsley.
Chill thoroughly; form into cylinders, pyramids or patties.
Dip into crumbs, then into slightly beaten egg mixed with 2 tablespoons of water and into crumbs again.
Chill.
Fry in hot deep fat (380°) until brown.
Serves 4.

title: very good brown bread
directions: Add enough bleached flour to work up.
Makes 5 loaves.
Bake approximately 40 minutes at 350°.

title: lu lu paste
directions: Cook together first five ingredients over medium heat until thickened. Add 8 oz. Philadelphia cream cheese. Whip until smooth. Add 1 jar pimentos, onions, green pepper.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Stir in pineapple and lemon juice.
Fold in bread cubes.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 25 to 40 minutes or until set.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: gefulltefisch(stuffed fish)
directions: Put butter in small saucepan and fry onion until golden brown. Add herbs, half the parsley, grated cheese, crumbled bread, paprika, egg, salt and pepper.
Season the fillets, cover half with mixture and fold over.
Arrange in a casserole and sprinkle with rest of filling.

Put a few slices of lemon on each fillet, cover with lid and bake at gas mark 4 (350°) for 10 minutes; then arrange tomatoes round fish and bake for a further 10 minutes. Replace used lemon slices with fresh before serving and decorate with rest of parsley or chives.

title: perfect corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal, flour, salt, sugar and baking powder in a large bowl.
Mix milk, eggs and oil in a separate bowl. Add to dry ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased muffin pans.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Put everything in a soup pot and cover with water (about 2 inches over vegetables). Cook until meat and vegetables are falling apart. Add green onions and parsley. Cook twenty minutes more and taste to see if more seasoning is needed.

title: no-cook chocolate fudge
directions: Melt cheese and butter together; add cocoa and nuts.
Mix together with powdered sugar.
Press onto a cookie sheet and refrigerate.
Can be frozen.

title: vanilla chip party mix(white chocolate party mix)
directions: Dissolve chocolate chips in vegetable oil.
Put all other ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour dissolved chocolate chips over ingredients in the large bowl.
Stir until ingredients are coated. Pour onto cookie sheets to cool.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add cinnamon, cloves and salt; stir in syrup.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well. Stir in oats.
Pour filling into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife inserted in center of pie comes out clean. Oatmeal forms chewy, nutty crust on top.

title: lulu paste
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until thick.
Add last 3 ingredients and mix together.
Put on favorite cracker.

title: jane's peanut brittle
directions: Cook syrup, water and sugar to hard ball stage (250° to 265°). Add peanuts and continue to cook, stirring occasionally until mixture is light brown in color (302°).
Stir in butter, soda and salt.
Pour on greased cookie sheet while still foaming.
Cool slightly and stretch to desired thinness and break into pieces.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Beat egg yolks; add lemon juice and rind.
Mix sugar, flour and salt to lemon mixture.
Stir in butter, then milk.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, then at 300° for 20 minutes or until filling is firm.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine the soup and sour cream in a bowl and mix well. Saute the chicken and onion in the butter in a skillet until the chicken is cooked through. Add half the sour cream mixture and mix well. Simmer for 10 minutes, stirring frequently. Spoon the chicken mixture onto the tortilla and roll to enclose the filling. Arrange the tortillas, seam side down, in a greased baking dish. Spread with the remaining sour cream mixture. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Sprinkle with the cheese. Bake just until the cheese melts.

title: angel food cake dessert
directions: Freeze angel food cake for easy slicing.
Put 1 cup milk in a bowl, add Dream Whip and vanilla.
Beat until it peaks.
In a medium bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar and 3 tablespoons milk until blended.
Fold Dream Whip mixture into cream cheese mixture.

title: quick yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and water and set aside.
Add to scalded milk, sugar, shortening, and salt.
When milk mixture is cool, add 2 cups plain flour and beat.
Add 1 egg and yeast.
Mix well.
Add 3 cups plain flour (or enough to make a soft dough that can be handled). Knead and place in greased bowl.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to use or use right away.
Roll out and cut as desired.
Let rise about 1 hour.
Bake at 425° for about 15 minutes.

title: paulet de normandie chicken
directions: Mix dressing mix, oleo and water.
Mix chicken, celery, onion, mayonnaise and salt.
Layer a large, lightly greased, baking pan with half of the dressing mixture.
Put chicken mixture over dressing mixture; add rest of dressing mix.
Beat together the eggs and milk.
Pour over casserole and refrigerate overnight. Take out; let set 1 hour before baking.
Spread the mushroom soup on top.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese; bake 10 minutes more.
Bake at 350°.
Serves 10.

title: oatmeal custard
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 325° oven for as long as it takes for crust to brown.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese and mix in sausage; mix well.
Add 1 cup of Bisquick and blend well, then another cup, blending well, then the last cup.
Shape into small balls and cook at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate chip supreme cookies
directions: Beat shortening and butter at medium speed until creamy; gradually add sugars.
Add eggs and beat.
Add mix and vanilla. Combine flour and next 4 ingredients.
Gradually add to butter mixture and beat.
Stir in morsels, pecans and oats.
Shape dough into balls and press to 1-inch thickness.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: our grandma's spaghetti and meat balls
directions: Chop garlic in butter.
Let fry for a minute or two.
Add tomato paste, water, allspice, salt and pepper and oil.
Cook until tender.

title: brother bruce's pasta sauce
directions: Brown the meat, onions, mushrooms and garlic in the olive oil. Add the tomato.
Add the wine, spices and chocolate to taste.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches in bottom of dish.
Mix sugar, flour, melted margarine, egg and flavoring.
Place loaf bread over peaches. Pour mixture over bread.
Bake at 325° until brown.

title: spaghetti creole
directions: Brown meat.
Drain off fat.
Add cans of tomato and onion. Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Break spaghetti into 3rds and cook.
Drain and add 1/2 stick of butter to spaghetti in pot.
Add meat mixture.
Add cheese.
Mix and put in casserole dish.
Heat through at 350°.

title: "texas trash"(texas version of party mix)
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Position rack in middle of oven.
Use 3-quart baking dish.
Melt together butter, hot pepper sauce, Worcestershire sauce, chili powder and oregano.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Cream shortening in bowl.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and egg.
Mix well.
Sift 2 cups flour with salt and baking powder; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Turn into greased 9-inch layer cake pan.
Sprinkle blueberries over batter.
Combine remaining sugar, remaining flour and cinnamon in small bowl; cut in margarine with pastry blender or 2 knives until crumbly. Sprinkle over blueberries.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sweet and tangy ham sauce
directions: Bring to boil.
Pour over ham loaf, then bake.

title: cookie hamburgers
directions: Place several vanilla wafers, flat side up, in a row.
Spread a layer of white frosting to look like mayonnaise on the wafers. Put a cup of coconut in a plastic bag with several drops of green food color.
Shake well; sprinkle on top of the wafers with frosting to look like lettuce.
Put a mint patty on each (looks like the meat).
Mix red and yellow food color to make orange and white frosting until it is cheese color; spread on patty.
Place another vanilla wafer on top of each, flat side down.
Take a paint brush; spread a small amount of honey on the bun tops and sprinkle with sesame seed.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix with other ingredients, except cheese and cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle cheese on top of casserole. Sprinkle cracker crumbs over cheese.
Bake in casserole, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: beans hawaiian
directions: Cook onion and butter until tender.
Mix all ingredients together and simmer.

title: supreme spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions. Drain and rinse in cold water. Place spaghetti in a large serving bowl; add the remaining ingredients and toss to coat. Cover and refrigerate for at least 45 minutes.

title: lemon-lime fish
directions: Mix first three ingredients, adding enough water to make a thick batter.
Grate peel of lemon and lime, add to the batter. Squeeze the juice from the lemon and lime and also add to the batter; mix well.
(If you like a thinner batter, add more water.) Coat pieces of fish in flour, then dip in batter.
Fry in hot oil. (To test oil to see if it's hot enough, stick a match in it, if the match lights, the oil is hot enough.)

title: mom's macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions (don't overcook).
Drain.
Dump macaroni into large oven casserole dish. Add milk; to determine if you have enough you should just be able to see it when looking at macaroni in dish.
No more.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add beaten egg.
Mix well.
Add chunks of Cheddar cheese.
The more the better.
Mix well.
Dot with margarine.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until all liquid is absorbed.
Don't stir while cooking.
Serves about 6 depending on how hungry!

title: gooey cake
directions: Crust:	Mix cake mix, oleo and 1 egg to make dough.
Press into 9 x 13 greased and floured pan.

title: grilled cheese
directions: Melt butter in a pan.
Grill bread to lightly brown on each side.
Put cheese between slices until melted.

title: beef, bean and biscuits
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Stir in next 5 ingredients; heat until bubbly.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Cut biscuits in half. Place cut side down around edge of casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Biscuits should be golden brown.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: new year's day bean soup
directions: Wash beans.
Place in 6-quart kettle.
Cover with 2 inches water over beans.
Add 2 tablespoons salt and soak overnight. Drain and add 2 quarts fresh water and ham.
Bring to a boil and simmer 3 hours.
Remove ham and cut up.
Add all remaining ingredients and ham pieces.
Simmer 1 hour longer.

title: jello salad
directions: Cook pineapple and sugar for 3 minutes.
Add to jello that has been dissolved in hot water.
Chill until syrupy, then add cheese and nuts.
Return to refrigerator until almost set, then fold in whipped cream.
Return to refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: potato candy
directions: Mix sugar, coconut and potato by hand.
Press into square 8 x 8-inch pan.
Spread chocolate over top.
Allow chocolate to dry. Cut into small squares.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Sift flour with sugar, baking powder and salt into bowl.
Cut in peanut butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add oats, egg and milk, stirring until blended.
Pour batter into greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove to rack to cool.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and cut eggplant into big pieces and cook in water with bay leaf.
When done, remove and drain well.
Put in bowl and mash with potato masher.
Saute in butter 1 large onion, celery and eggplant.
Next, add to the eggplant the mixture of grated cheese and Velveeta cheese.
Then add basil, curry, chili powder, paprika, garlic (which has been mashed) and soy sauce.
Drain mushrooms and pimentos.
Mash real well and add egg yolks, salt and pepper.
Put in buttered casserole and cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Put cucumbers and sliced onions in a large pan.
Pour salt over them.
Cover with ice.
Let set 3 hours.
Heat spices, sugar and vinegar.
Drain cucumbers and onions.
Add to spice mix. Bring to boil.
Put in jars to seal.
Makes 6 to 7 quarts.

title: hospitality chicken soup
directions: After cleaning chicken, put in a 6-quart pot filled with 4 to 5 quarts of water.
Let it come to a boil and skim off scum (the discolored foam that rises to the top).
When soup looks clear, add all other ingredients.
Let it come to a boil, then lower. Cover with venting and let simmer until chicken falls off the bone.
Strain and serve.

title: peanut butter frosting
directions: Combine milk and margarine in saucepan.
Heat until butter melts.
Pour over sugar; blend.
Add peanut butter.
Beat until well mixed and good spreading consistency.

title: "eat all you want" lo-cal soup
directions: Boil squash and onions in water for 15 minutes.
Add green beans, tomatoes, tomato sauce, soup mix and spaghetti.
Simmer about 20 to 30 minutes.
Deliciously low calorie and low-fat.
(You may add other lo-cal vegetables as desired:
carrots, celery, cabbage, okra, etc.)

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix apples and water in a 9-inch pan.
Mix together butter, flour, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: papa's italian spaghetti
directions: Brown sausage, garlic and onion in margarine.
Add all ingredients and simmer for two hours.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Combine in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 4 hours.

title: sinful salad
directions: Combine Jell-O and water; stir until dissolved.
Cool; add bananas, nuts, strawberries and pineapple to Jell-O and stir until blended.
Divide this mixture in 2 parts; pour 1/2 into 8 x 12-inch pan.
Refrigerate about 1 hour (keep remainder at room temperature).
Spread sour cream over partially set Jell-O.
Pour remainder over sour cream.
Cover and refrigerate until set, about 1 1/2 hours or overnight.
Serves 12.

title: pina colada slush
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in freezer.
Fill with half slush and half Seven-Up or Sprite.

title: hankie pankies
directions: Fry ground beef and sausage. Drain.
Add Velveeta (cut into chunks).
Stir until melted. Spread on rye bread slices. May be frozen. No need to thaw.
Put in oven at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Spray nonstick skillet with vegetable cooking spray.
Heat 1 minute.
Stir-fry chicken in 2 batches until browned.
Remove skillet from heat.
Remove chicken.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash sweet potatoes with melted butter.
Add sugar, milk, eggs and vanilla and mix well.
Put into greased casserole dish.

title: goulash
directions: Brown beef and rice.
Add all other ingredients, except rice. Add 1/2 cup water and bring to a boil.
Add rice and reduce heat. Simmer until rice is done.
Add a small amount of water, if it gets too dry.

title: ashley's favorite chocolate dream pie
directions: Combine first four ingredients and "pat" into 9 x 13-inch pan (will be a thin crust).
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until light brown.
Allow to cool.
Beat next two ingredients and spread over crust.
Beat pudding and milk and put on top.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with crushed walnuts. Chill for 2 hours.
Enjoy.

title: ham and cheese stuffed potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Scrub potatoes and pat dry.
Rub each potato with shortening.
Prick several places with fork.
Bake for about 1 hour or until done.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise. Scoop out inside, leaving a thin shell.

title: fruit punch
directions: Combine sugar, water, Kool-Aid and 3 juices.
Add ginger ale.

title: sausage dip
directions: Brown beef and sausage until done.
Add to melted Velveeta cheese.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serve with tacos from a chafing dish.
Hot!
Serves many.

title: banana cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 8-inch square pan.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add eggs, salad oil, vanilla and mashed bananas.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in chopped dates and nuts. Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: brown rice
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Cover and put in oven at 400° about 30 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.

title: crescent rolls
