directions: First, mix yeast (if you use powdered yeast, mix with 1/4 cup warm water) and 1 tablespoon sugar in a bowl.
Then add eggs, 1/2 cup sugar, shortening, salt and warm milk.
Mix in flour.
(You don't have to knead the dough.)
Leave bowl in the refrigerator overnight.

title: diabetic banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding as directed.
Add 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Layer bananas, vanilla wafers and pudding.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: oven porcupines
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix well meat, rice, 1/2 cup water, onion, salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Shape mixture into balls, place in ungreased baking dish (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Stir together remaining ingredients; pour over meat balls.
Cover with foil.
Bake 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake additional 15 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Use juice from fruit to equal 4 cups.
Add water if needed to make 4 cups.
Pour into saucepan.
Add both puddings to saucepan and bring to boil.
Remove from heat and let cool completely.
Mix in fruit and chill.

title: tropical fruit punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in a punch bowl with ice ring (recipe below) and serve.
Garnish as desired.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Mix together.
Bring to a boil; thicken with cornstarch.

title: super corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add corn and cheese; mix well.
Mix cornmeal, flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add dry ingredients and green chilies to bowl.
Mix well.
Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour in batter.
Bake for 30 minutes, until a light brown.

title: clam chowder
directions: Cover with water and cook potatoes, carrots, celery, onion and ham or bacon.
When tender, add clams, soup and cube.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Add 2 cans milk.
Heat, but do not boil.

title: mom's hot dish
directions: Put uncooked
noodles
in
a
greased
9 x 13-inch pan. Brown beef
and onions and spread over noodles.
Mix spaghetti sauce, water
and	sugar
and
simmer
minutes.
Pour
over noodles. Cover tightly and bake at 325° about 1 hour or until noodles are tender.
Add cheese on top 15 minutes before it is done.

title: sirloin tips
directions: Coat skillet with Pam spray; add garlic.
As pieces brown, remove to 1-quart casserole with a cover.
Add 1/4 cup wine to the skillet.
Saute mushrooms; add to meat.
Microcook wine and mushrooms on High for 3 1/2 to 4 minutes, stirring each minute. Cover and bake slowly at 275° for 1 hour, until meat is tender.

title: creamy italian sub sandwich
directions: Mix dressing and Italian dressing.
Toss lettuce with 1/4 cup of the dressing mixture.
Brush cut surfaces of rolls with remaining dressing mixture.
Fill rolls with meat, process cheese food, vegetables and lettuce mixture.
Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: new orleans catfish
directions: Cut fish into serving size portions and place in a well-greased baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Sprinkle fish with salt and pepper. Combine rice, onion and curry powder; spread over fish.
Top with lemon slices and dot with butter.
Cover and bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Remove cover the last few minutes of cooking to allow for slight browning.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream the brown sugar and butter.
Stir in baking mix and walnuts until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup.
Press remaining mixture in a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions and drain. Pour drained broccoli back into cooking pan.
Stir in cheese and 1/2 of the butter, until melted.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Melt remaining butter.
Stir in crackers.
Sprinkle crackers over broccoli.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes.

title: cheesy apple ham grill
directions: Mix apple, 1/3 cup of the dressing, walnuts and cloves.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Pull corned beef apart; add other ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Place in buttered casserole.
Top with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Add more cheese, if wanted.

title: easy skillet beef "stew" and noodles
directions: Prepare noodles as label directs, using 1 teaspoon salt in water.
Trim any fat from flank steak.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch chunks.
Thinly slice carrots and onions.
Cut mushrooms in half. Combine soy sauce, catsup, cornstarch and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Add flank steak pieces and stir mixture gently until meat is well coated.
Add 4 teaspoons of oil to skillet and cook carrots and onions until tender-crisp and lightly browned.
Add 2 more teaspoons of oil and cook mushrooms until tender.
Add steak mixture and cook about 3 to 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: juicy cinnamon warmer
directions: Place tea bags in water for 4 minutes.
Remove bags, squeezing excess water out.
Add juices and sugar.
Heat to near boiling.
Serve hot.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients listed.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients and spread in pan.
Bake until golden brown, about 25 minutes.
Cut into 1 x 2-inch pieces.
Makes four dozen appetizers.

title: buttery pan rolls
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Let stand until bubbly (about 15 minutes).
Stir together 2 cups of flour, the sugar and salt until well mixed.
Add 6 tablespoons of the melted butter, the egg, yeast mixture and milk.
Beat about 5 minutes to blend well.
Gradually beat in remaining 2 1/2 cups flour.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until double, about 45 minutes.
Pour 1/2 of remaining butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat down butter and drop by spoonfuls into buttered pan, making 15 rolls.
Drizzle remaining butter over top.
Cover and let rise until double (30 minutes).
Bake in a preheated oven (425°) for 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: never fail dumplings
directions: Mix ingredients except soups and roll on floured board.
Cut in strips and drop in near boiling broth.
Simmer with lid on.
Gently stir occasionally.
Add to your broth where chicken has been cooked:
cream of chicken soup and cream of celery soup (undiluted).
If you have only a small amount of broth, add 1 can water.

title: wassail christmas drink
directions: Mix all together and simmer for 30 minutes. Makes a delicious Christmas drink.

title: ginger crinkles
directions: Beat together margarine and brown sugar, add egg and molasses. Sift dry ingredients together and mix well.
Chill 1 hour.
Make into small ball and roll in granulated sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar, shortening and butter together. Add flour and eggs, a little at a time, alternately to sugar mixture.
Add lemon extract and pour into floured pan.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: kabak dolmasi(turkish stuffed zucchini)
directions: Cook rice, cool.
Combine beef, rice, milk, onion, 1 teaspoon salt, mint and pepper. Mix well.
Peel zucchini.
Cut off both ends of zucchini, scoop out centers and chop.
Reserve chopped centers.
Fill zucchini loosely with meat mixture, make meat balls with leftovers.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Slice carrots; cook and drain.
Melt butter and cheese together.
Put carrots in casserole dish.
Pour cheese mixture over carrots.
Crumble up Ritz crackers on top.

title: easy lemon pies(makes two pies)
directions: Fold together condensed milk, frozen lemonade and Cool Whip. Pour into graham cracker crusts and place in freezer.

title: meatballs to can
directions: Mix lightly until blended.
Shape into small balls; a cantaloup baller works good.
Place on baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or less, until they are firm.
Pack in jars and add juice mixture.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put in 9-inch pie dish.
Grate Mozzarella cheese over top.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. Serve with Breton crackers.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Put in large pan.
Boil sugar, water and corn syrup without stirring, until it cracks when tried in cold water (260°).
Add vinegar, salt and vanilla.
Boil until mixture reaches 264° or it spins a thread.
Pour slowly over corn, turning with a spoon to coat each kernel.
Working quickly with greased hands, form into balls.
Let stand until brittle.

title: dreamsicle cake
directions: Prepare orange cake mix according to package directions, except use milk in place of water and add orange flavoring.
Bake as directed in 2 (9-inch or 8-inch) pans.
Cool completely.
When cooled, slice each layer crosswise, making 4 layers.

title: hermit squares
directions: Put sugar and oil in a bowl; mix.
Sift together and add to that the flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add milk, molasses, raisins and chopped nuts.
Spread on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar while hot.

title: amanda's karo popcorn mixture
directions: Prepare popcorn.
In 3-quart saucepan.
Mix Karo syrup, margarine, water, vinegar, confectioners sugar and cut-up marshmallows.
Stir over low heat until mixture starts to boil. Pour over popcorn.
Toss to coat.

title: rich drop sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar with margarine until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Stir in the oil.
Add the sifted dry ingredients; blend well.
Refrigerate until chilled thoroughly.
Form into balls.
Place on cookie sheet; flatten with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake in a 350° oven until lightly browned.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into a baked 8-inch pie crust. Refrigerate.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Combine sausage and sage.
Salt outside of hard-boiled eggs. Using 2 tablespoons of sausage per egg, wrap eggs.
Chill to allow sausage to set.
Fry in Wesson oil.
Drain well.
Eggs may be halved and passed at brunch as an appetizer.

title: eggnog
directions: Combine eggs, condensed milk, vanilla and salt until thoroughly blended. Gradually blend in milk. Gently fold in whipped cream. Sprinkle nutmeg to taste. Let sit a couple of days for best flavor.

title: veg-all pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in pie shell.
Cover with other pie shell and bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: yogurt dressing(salt-free)
directions: Put yogurt into small bowl.
Add vinegar, garlic, tarragon, parsley, black pepper to taste and the mustard.
Mix well and pour over salad.

title: hawaiian banana nut bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until batter is moistened.
Spoon batter into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 65 minutes or until done.
Cool completely.
Yield:
2 loaves.

title: bread pudding
directions: Break the bread into small pieces and mix with remaining ingredients.
Bake in slow oven for 45 minutes or until done.

title: hot pineapple cranberry punch
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a 10 to 12-cup electric percolator.
Place brown sugar and remaining ingredients in percolator basket.
Perk through complete cycle.
Serve hot. Yields 6 cups.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: chess squares
directions: Heat butter and sugar over low heat.
Add other ingredients in order given.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Bake for 40 to 50 minutes in a 300° oven.
Cut into squares.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix ingredients with 2 1/2 cups of the flour.
Beat for 3 minutes.
Stir in remaining flour to make
a
soft
dough. Knead for 8 minutes.
Place dough in greased
bowl
and
turn over. Cover with linen cloth and let
rise
overnight.
Next morning, punch down and divide into 3 parts.
Shape into round loaves and place on greased cookie sheets.
Cover and let rise until double (6 to 10 hours).
Bake at 350°
for
minutes. Brush with butter, if desired.
Cool on rack.
Makes 3 loaves. Alternatively, 3 small loaves (8 1/2 x 4 1/2
x
2 1/2-inches) or 2 large loaves (9 x 5 x 3-inches) can be made.

title: shirley's drop cookies(microwave recipe)
directions: In large bowl, combine margarine and milk.
Microwave (High) 45 seconds.
Blend with sugar, cocoa and salt.
Microwave (High) 6 minutes, stirring twice, until boiling.
Add vanilla and peanut butter until well mixed.
Blend in oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoonful onto wax paper.
Cool until firm, 1 to 2 hours.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: pasta shells florentine
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix spinach, Mozzarella cheese, Ricotta cheese, egg white and Parmesan cheese until blended.
Fill each cooked shell with spinach mixture.
Place in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Spoon sauce over shells. Cover with foil.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: beef stew
directions: Cut into chunks the desired amount of carrots, potatoes, celery and onions.
To vegetables, add desired amount of beef cubes, 1 can cream of mushroom soup, 1 can tomato soup and 2 bay leaves.
Add enough water to cover.
Stir.
Bake in 350° oven for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: baked beans
directions: Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: tuna chop suey
directions: Mix all the ingredients together (except chips) and bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Remove from oven and cover the top with potato chips.
Bake 1/2 hour more.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine crackers, peanut butter and vanilla; set aside. Butter a dish or pan.
Bring to a rolling boil the sugar and milk; boil for 3 minutes.
Put in other mixture and mix well.

title: prune cake
directions: Cream first 2 ingredients. Add eggs, beating well after each. Add dry ingredients alternately with sour milk or buttermilk. Add prunes. Bake at 350° in 2 layers of sheet cake pan. Check after 25 minutes for doneness.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook rice in chicken broth; chill.
In large bowl, mix chicken, peas and onion.
Add rice.
Toss well.
Add dressing. Garnish with tomato.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: stir-fried chicken and rice
directions: In large skillet heat 2 tablespoons oil over medium-high heat. Add broccoli, carrots, walnuts and garlic.
Stir-fry 2 minutes. Remove vegetables.
Add remaining 2 tablespoons oil to skillet. Add chicken; stir-fry 1 minute or until chicken turns white.
Add soy sauce, sherry, ginger and sugar.
Stir-fry 2 minutes.
Remove chicken with slotted spoon.

title: 3-quart barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients, except ketchup and boil for 8 minutes.
Add ketchup and boil 2 minutes more.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in 9-inch round cake pans.
Cool and then cut layers into and fill with cooked lemon pudding and pie filling.
Frost cake with lemon frosting.

title: yogurt dessert sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir well.
Makes enough for 8 servings (about 2 cups).
Use with baked apples, fresh strawberries or any other fruit dessert.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Place unbeaten egg whites, sugar, syrup and water in double boiler.
Whip with rotary (or electric mixer) beater until mixture is stiff.
Remove from fire; add 1 teaspoon vanilla.

title: "celeri ordinare"(brazil celery)
directions: Note:
For a simple variation, substitute Chablis for vermouth and add 1/2 cup fine chopped Brazil nuts.

title: four layer dessert
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix flour, butter and pecans and mash into bottom of baking dish (large).
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Mix and pat in 9 x 13 baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: prime rib roast(served at the annual centurion dinner)
directions: Bring the meat to room temperature by removing it from the refrigerator at least an hour before cooking, preferably two. Preheat oven to 450°.
Place meat, bone side down, in a large roasting pan.
Season with salt and pepper.
If you like garlic, peel cloves and cut into tiny slivers.
Use a small, sharp knife to poke small holes in the meat and insert garlic.
Place roast in oven and cook 15 minutes undisturbed.
Turn heat down to 350° and roast 1 hour.
Check in several places with an instant-read meat thermometer.
When no spot checks in at under 125°, the meat is rare.
Cook for another 5 or 10 minutes if you like it more done, then check again, but in no case let the temperature go above 155°.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar; add soup and rest of ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: ricotta pie(southern italy)
directions: Whip eggs, Ricotta, sugar and vanilla.
Add orange and lemon juice, grated orange and lemon peel.
Blend well.

title: great microwave lasagna
directions: Combine onions, garlic and oil in a 5-quart casserole. Microwave at High 3 1/2 minutes, or until onions are tender-crisp, stirring once.
Crumble ground beef into onion mixture.
Cover; microwave 10 to 14 minutes, or until meat loses its pink color, stirring 2 or 3 times.
Microwave green pepper in a small covered bowl for 2 to 3 minutes, or until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients for the beef mixture with exception of cheeses; microwave 7 to 10 minutes, or until hot and bubbly, stirring 2 to 3 times.
Cook noodles conventionally while microwaving sauce.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar, cornmeal and cocoa; mix well.
Add eggs; beat well.
Then add corn syrup and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes in non-preheated oven.

title: sweet and sour meatballs with rice
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice. add water to juice if necessary to equal 1 cup liquid.
In skillet, add 1/3 c water, vinegar, soy sauce, brown sugar, corn starch.
Stir until smooth. Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Add pineapple, green pepper and rice.
Simmer uncovered for 20 minutes.

title: caramel icing
directions: Mix brown sugar, cream and butter and bring to a boil.
Remove from fire and cool slightly.
Add vanilla and powdered sugar to spread nicely.

title: spicy rice dip
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add all other ingredients except sour cream.
Simmer 10 or 15 minutes.
Add sour cream; heat but do not boil.
Serve with chips.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Beat butter, egg and powdered sugar.
Add the rest.
Chill.

title: old-fashioned shake
directions: Combine ingredients.
Beat or blend until smooth.
Serve at once in glasses.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix mustard, soy sauce and vinegar.
Pour over vegetables and toss.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: jello cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix together all ingredients.
Roll dough into small balls and flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes.

title: vegetable burrito salad
directions: Beat together oil, lemon juice, basil, salt and pepper in small bowl.
Lightly brush on vegetables before grilling.
Brush vegetables again each time they're turned.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco.
Add sugar and cream some more.
Add beaten eggs and beat well.
Sift flour, salt, baking powder and cocoa together.
Add to creamed mixture with the milk.
Add vanilla.

title: easy, never fail caramel cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients until creamy in a large bowl.
Cream 2 minutes until smooth.
Beat egg whites until frothy. Add baking powder and beat until stiff.
Fold whites and vanilla into mixture.
Pour into greased and floured pans (Makes 2 thick or 3 thin layers).
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes good cupcakes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters and drop into brown paper bag with sugar and cinnamon.
Shake until coated well.
Drop into greased tube pan and sprinkle with pecans.
Bring to boil sugar, brown sugar, evaporated milk and margarine.
Pour this mixture over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Turn pan upside-down on large plate immediately after removing.
Serves 12.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Put eggs and sugar into a large bowl and mix.
Add milk, vanilla, whipping cream and salt.
Pour mixture into an ice cream container and put it into the ice cream maker.
Fill ice cream maker with ice.
Add handfuls of rock salt to the ice.
Freeze until ice cream is firm, about 30 minutes.
Serve.
Makes 1 gallon of ice cream.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Make sauce by cooking onion, pepper and hamburger until has all turned color.
Add tomato soup and olives.
Cook noodles and drain.
In long dish, make layers of noodles, sauce and cheese, ending with cheese.
On top of these layers, now pour the mushroom soup.
Put in oven at about 400° and bake until cheese all looks melted and is bubbly.

title: velveeta nacho chip dip
directions: Mix all together and heat through.
Dip nacho chips in mix.

title: rye dill dip
directions: Combine ingredients and refrigerate 6 to 8 hours.
Hollow out large, round, unsliced loaf of Bohemian rye with caraway.
Place dip in hollow of bread and serve.

title: mulled cider
directions: Put ingredients together in pot.
Boil, then simmer for 10 minutes.
Strain.
Put in crock-pot to keep warm.
So good on cold days!

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Arrange eggplant, tomato and onion slices in layers in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup margarine on top. Sprinkle basil over that.
Baked covered for 20 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Stir crumbs into remaining margarine and sprinkle over cheese.
Top with Parmesan cheese and bacon (optional).
Bake uncovered 10 minutes or until bubbly.

title: potato cheese scallop
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add cheese, then half and half. When thoroughly melted and mixed, pour over frozen potatoes in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: poor man's stroganoff
directions: Cook noodles.
Sear beef.
Add other ingredients.
Place in buttered casserole dish and top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oreo fudge pie
directions: Spread ice cream in crust; top with fudge sauce.
Freeze until firm, about 6 hours.
To serve, garnish pie with whipped topping.

title: pizza dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, oregano and sour cream.
Spread into a quiche pan or pie plate.
Top with pizza sauce.
Sprinkle with green pepper, pepperoni and onion.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Add Mozzarella cheese and bake until melted.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Melt margarine and butter.
Add sugar, eggs, vinegar and vanilla and mix.
Add coconut and nuts.
Put in unbaked pie shell. Place in preheated oven (350°).
Bake until the pie shakes together, approximately 25 to 30 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch cake pan; spread pineapple, then cherry filling. Crumble dry cake mix over fruits. Slice oleo and lay over cake mix. Completely cover.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Put potatoes in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt margarine and mix with sour cream, soup, cheese and onion.
Pour over potatoes. Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: rolled oats cake
directions: Pour the boiling water over the oats; let stand for 20 minutes.
Cream together the shortening or margarine, sugars and eggs.
Add the remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in an 8 x 11-inch or 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread topping on hot cake.

title: super bowl stew
directions: Brown the cubed beef in the olive oil, then add the onions and garlic.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Add the cumin, chili powder and salt; cook another minute.
Add the picante sauce, smoked sausage (which has been cut into pieces) and the quartered tomatoes to the beef mixture.
Cook for 45 minutes.
Add cut up potatoes and pepper; cook for another 30 minutes, or until potatoes are done. Serves 4.

title: van's cheese cake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, melted butter and 1/4 cup sugar. Blend ingredients well.
Press into greased spring-form pan. Bake for 8 minutes. Cool.
Combine cornstarch, 1/4 cup sugar and pineapple. Cook over medium heat, stirring briskly, until mixture is clear and thickened.
Cool.
Spread pineapple mixture over crust.
Beat cream cheese, egg yolks, 3/4 cup sugar, vanilla and lemon juice in a blender until smooth.

Beat 1 1/2 cups sour cream into cheese mixture until smooth and well blended. Beat egg whites and add salt until stiff peaks form. Fold egg whites carefully into cheese mixture. Do not beat, but blend well.
Pour carefully on top of pineapple mixture.
Make sure pan is securely locked.
Place in heated oven (300°) and bake 1 1/2 hours or until set and brown. Turn off heat; open oven door.
Let cool in oven 1/2 hour.
Remove from oven.
Cool thoroughly.
Before serving, spoon remaining sour cream over cake and garnish with lemon rind.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine milk, margarine and sugar in large pan.
Bring to boil over low heat for 5 minutes.
Then add bitter chocolate, chocolate chips, Marshmallow Whip and nuts.
Stir until fully dissolved. Pour in buttered pan and cool.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: fran's easy broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine (not butter).
Melt Velveeta cheese.
Lightly cook chopped broccoli.
Mix all and put into casserole.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and cream cheese until light and fluffy. Add salt and vanilla; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in flour.
Spoon mixture into a greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: orange and lemon salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups of hot water. Add 1/2 cup of cold water and let partially congeal. Then add drained pineapple and let congeal until firm.

title: fried sausage cheese fondue
directions: Thirty minutes before serving, dip sausages and cheeses into the beaten egg and dip each into the bread crumbs.
Repeat, covering with 2 layers of coating.

title: mexican chicken soup
directions: Place chicken pieces in large saucepan.
Add enough water to cover.
Cook until tender, about 25 minutes.
Remove chicken pieces from the broth and add tomatoes, garlic, onion and chilies. Slide chicken meat off the bones and return meat to the broth. Add beans and simmer about 15 minutes.
Serve with tortillas. Yield:
About 2 quarts.
Approximate calories/serving:
1 cup = 190, 1 tortilla = 60.

title: creole fish fry
directions: Mix milk and mustard. In a separate bowl, mix Creole spices and cornmeal. Dip the fish in the milk-mustard mixture and then cornmeal. Heat a skillet with oil. Fry fish until flaky.

title: pasta salad
directions: Combine ingredients and chill.

title: sinner's delight
directions: Blend first three ingredients.
Batter will be stiff.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Cream the cheese with sugar, fold in Cool Whip.
Spread cream cheese mixture onto cooled crust.
Mix together pudding and milk, spread onto cream cheese mixture.
Add rest of Cool Whip.
Use large container to spread over pudding.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts, if desired.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Line chicken in bottom of casserole.
Mix the next 4 ingredients in a bowl; spread broccoli over chicken, then pour the ingredients over the broccoli.
Then spread cheese over it and bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour.
(If you like onions, add some chopped onion over broccoli.)

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and margarine; add sugar and eggs and mix well.
Blend in flour alternating with the milk.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: classy carrot cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan and line with waxed paper.
Grease paper.
Mix first 7 ingredients.
Beat until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pan.
Bake 1 hour or until cake pulls away from pan.
Cool.
Turn out and peel paper.

title: cherry whip cake icing
directions: Bring sugar, jello, pineapple and water to boil and simmer 5 minutes; chill until set.
Add Cool Whip and mix with the other ingredients.
Put on angel food cake, filling the hole and covering.
Refrigerate.

title: pete's blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a muffin pan or use foil baking cups.
In a medium size bowl, beat butter until creamy.
Beat in sugar until fluffy and pale.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Beat in vanilla, baking powder and salt.
Mix mashed blueberries into batter.
Fold in half of flour, then half the milk.
Add remaining flour and milk.
Fold in remaining blueberries.

title: white apple brownies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in apple and nuts.
Bake in a greased 8 x 12-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cut in bars.
When cool, roll in powdered sugar.

title: cherry cake
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar, eggs, vanilla, milk and vinegar.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Pour into 8 x 12-inch greased and lightly floured pan.
Dot top of cake mix with cherry pie filling before baking.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes 16 servings.

title: chicken pie with crust
directions: Cook chicken breast with celery and onion, along with salt and pepper, it will improve the flavor. Cool. Cut into bite size pieces.
Mix with soup and broth.
Heat to boiling.
Grease a 2-quart casserole dish, put chicken in and sprinkle with chopped eggs.
Pour broth over all.
Make a mixture of butter, flour, pepper and milk.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Be sure not to stir. Bake in 425° oven for 30 minutes.

title: ham hocks and turnip greens
directions: Wash greens, breaking off the tough stems.
Cook the ham hocks for about 1 hour, then cut up greens with season to taste.
Let cook for 2 to 3 hours on low heat.

title: prune bread
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl, except the walnuts, and mix well.
Add nuts.
Bake in a small greased loaf pans at 350° for 1/2 hour, then reduce heat to 325° and bake for 1/2 hour.
Let cool for 25 minutes or so, then remove from pans and cool on racks.
Keeps well in refrigerator or freezes well.
(I use three 3 1/2 x 7 x 2-inch deep pans.)

title: big jim's potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes thinly being careful not to slice completely through potato (so that potato stays together).
In between every few cuts in potato, place onion slice and pat of butter.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and garlic salt.
Sprinkle on herbs if desired.
Place potato on foil sheet and wrap up tightly.
Cook on grill for 25-35 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
May also be cooked in oven or campfire.

title: zesty meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, egg, onion and salt.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Cook at 400° for 10 minutes (5 minutes each side).
Combine chili sauce, jelly, lemon juice and hot sauce.
Cook over medium heat until jelly melts.
Simmer meatballs with sauce for 5 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream
shortening, butter or margarine, brown sugar and white sugar
together.
Add eggs.
Sift flour again with soda and
salt. Stir in mixture.
Add oatmeal, vanilla and walnuts or pecans. Mix well.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: In a large skillet, brown chicken in oil. Add onion, green pepper and garlic and cook about 2 minutes to soften a bit.

title: lemon barbecue chicken
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except chicken.
Heat on stove, but do not boil.
Dip chicken in sauce and barbecue.
Keep dipping chicken every time you turn the chicken, every 5 minutes or so.
You can also precook chicken by pouring sauce over chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan and heat on the stove for about 10 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add egg.
Add alternately with the applesauce the cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg, flour and soda, then add the nuts, raisins, chopped dates and vanilla.
Bake in greased pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Melt and mix together the first 3 ingredients.
In a large bowl, combine marshmallows and peanuts.
Mix melted ingredients with marshmallows and nuts.
Spread in a 10 x 15-inch pan; line pan with wax paper.
Chill for 2 hours.
Cut into pieces.

title: coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Measure 2/3 cup of cake mix (dry mix) into small bowl. Cut in the butter. Mix in brown sugar and nuts. Set aside. Beat eggs lightly with a fork; stir in sour cream. Blend in remaining cake mix (dry mix), scraping bowl often. (Batter will be thick and slightly lumpy.) Pour half the batter into greased and floured oblong pan, 13 x 9
x 2-inches. Sprinkle half the topping over batter. Spoon and gently spread remaining batter into pan; top with remaining topping mixture. Bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chess-buttery cake
directions: Combine 1 box dry cake mix, 1 stick softened margarine and 1 egg.
Spread mixture into the bottom of a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Set aside.
Combine cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 2 eggs.
Beat mixture well and pour onto "dough" in pan. Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Cut into squares.

title: bow cookies
directions: Cut flour into oleo and blend in cream cheese.
Form into a ball and refrigerate overnight.
Roll thin and cut into squares (2-inches) and fill with your favorite filling (about 1/2 teaspoon).
Roll in flour and sugar.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: * lorado chili *
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion and green pepper.
Cook until tender. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cranberry-apple conserve
directions: Peel, core and chop apples, reserving 1/2 peelings.
Cut oranges into thinnest possible slices and remove seeds.
Place oranges, reserved apple peelings and water; let simmer over moderate heat until the skin of the oranges is tender.
Strain, reserving liquid.
Discard apple peelings.
Cut each orange slice into 8 small sections.
Chop cranberries and add to apples, oranges and liquid.
Cook until thick, about 40 minutes.
Stir frequently. Add walnuts during the last 5 minutes.
Ladle into clean 1/2 pints and seal.
Process 10 to 15 minutes in hot water bath.

title: pay day cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, margarine and egg.
Pat in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° until done.
Remove from oven; cover with 3 cups miniature marshmallows.
Set aside.
Mix white syrup, margarine, butterscotch chips and vanilla.
Heat until melted. Add Rice Krispies and peanuts.
Spread over marshmallows (I use light cake mix and light margarine and unsalted peanuts).

title: pancakes
directions: Beat egg and add remaining ingredients in order given.
Beat with rotary beater.
Pour batter from pitcher or tip of spoon onto greased griddle.
Pancakes are ready to turn when they are puffed and full of bubbles, before bubbles break.
After turning, cook until golden brown.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown beef, add soup and veggies and stir until warm through. Place in 9 x 13-inch pan and spread evenly.
Add egg to the potatoes.
Scoop potatoes on top of meat mixture and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves approximately 6.

title: chicken pot pie 2
directions: Mix together and pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour crust over top and bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix with electric mixer.

title: whipper snapper cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together with mixer.
With hands, form into 1-inch balls.
Roll in powdered sugar; flatten out on greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Do not overbake. Remove from pan while hot.

title: world's best brownies(can be made in one pan)
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate in a double boiler (or in microwave for about 2 minutes).
Remove from heat and add sugar. Stir well.
Add eggs and mix thoroughly.
Add flour and beat only until flour is incorporated.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a 9-inch square pan which has been greased with margarine or sprayed with Baker's Joy.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
(I then roll them lightly in powdered sugar.)
Makes about 16 squares.

title: taco twist
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Stir in seasoning mix, tomato sauce and green pepper.
Bring to a boil and remove from heat. Combine cooked macaroni, 1/2 of the cheese and sour cream.
Place in bottom of a baking dish.
Top with meat mixture and remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with nacho or taco chips.

title: mile high pie
directions: First Layer:
Melt oleo.
Add flour and pecans.
Pat into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°, then cool.

title: polynesian meat ball sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan and simmer 10 minutes. Serve with your favorite meat ball recipe.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: strawberry-banana split pie
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and 1/2 cup melted butter; stir well. Press crumb mixture into a 9-inch square baking pan.
Combine egg and remaining 1/2 cup butter.
Stir in powdered sugar and pour over crust.

title: bread pudding(diabetic)
directions: Soak bread cubes in scalded milk for 5 minutes; add sugar substitute, cinnamon and raisins.
Pour bread mixture slowly over beaten eggs.
Add vanilla and blend well.
Pour into a greased baking dish; bake in a slow 325° oven about 50 minutes, until firm.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tropical pork salad
directions: Combine ham, noodles, green pepper and celery in a bowl. Drain pineapple chunks; reserve 2 tablespoons juice.
Add pineapple chunks to salad ingredients.
Combine and mix salad dressing, pineapple juice, ginger and salt.
Mix well.
Pour over salad ingredients; toss lightly to coat evenly.
Cover.
Chill well.
Serve on salad greens.

title: congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups of hot water. Add cream cheese to the jello mixture. Add other ingredients. Pour in dish and place in refrigerator to jell.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and boil until tender.
Combine with remaining ingredients and put in casserole dish.
Cook at 350° until bubbly. Serves 10 to 12.

title: vadas
directions: Soak chickpeas and urd dhal (which you get in Indian stores) for about 2 hours.
Drain all the water and grind coarsely with dry red chillies.
The ground mixture should be solid, not loose.
Cut onions, green chillies and ginger into small pieces and mix it with the ground mixture.
Take a tablespoon of mixture, put in your hands or in a plastic sheet and fry in oil until golden brown. Serve hot with ketchup.

title: dorita pie
directions: Saute onion.
Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Mix onion, meat, beans, Ro-Tel and soups in large skillet and heat thoroughly. Place Doritos in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: yummy potatoes
directions: Cook the potatoes in salted water with a bay leaf.
When cold, peel and grate coarsely.
Put potatoes in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together the soup, melted margarine, sour cream, salt, pepper, onion and 1 1/2 cups grated cheese and pour over potatoes. Cover; bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Sprinkle top with 1/2 cup grated cheese and the crushed potato chips.
Bake a few minutes more.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll cookies in small balls.
Dip fork in sugar; mash cookies.
Cook on cookie sheet, 10 to 12 minutes.

title: peter paul mound cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed on box.
Make 4 thin layers.

title: oatmeal-raisin pockets
directions: Stir
together	flour,	cinnamon,
baking powder, salt, baking soda
and	nutmeg.
In a large mixer bowl, beat butter until softened.
Add brown sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla
and beat well.
Add flour mixture and beat until well mixed.
Stir in oats.
Shape into 2 (7-inch) rolls.
Wrap and chill for 6 hours or overnight.

title: pea salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order.
Mix sour cream, salad dressing and sugar in separate bowl and pour over salad.
Put another layer of ingredients with more topping over them.
Cover with Cheddar cheese and bacon bits.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: crunchy nut cookies
directions: Mix sugars, shortening, eggs and vanilla until creamy.
Sift together flour, soda and salt, then add to other ingredients; add nuts.
Shape 1 level tablespoon of dough into balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and flatten with bottom of greased glass. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: raleigh's rollovers
directions: Roll Pippin Hot loaf; cut into 4 x 4-inch squares.
Spread Dijon mustard onto center of dough.
(Use as much or as little as you like.)
Mix cheese and ham.
Put 1 to 2 teaspoons of mixture into center of dough.
Fold dough into triangles.
Seal edges. Bake on cookie sheet at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken and sausage creole
directions: In skillet on high, heat oil.
Add chicken and brown, stirring quickly.
Add peppers, sausage and onion.
Saute until vegetables are limp.
Stir constantly.
Add broth.
When broth boils, add rice.
Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes until liquid is absorbed.
Sprinkle on pepper flakes and stir in when fluffing rice.

title: buttermilk fruit salad
directions: Mix milk and pudding.
Fold in Cool Whip and well drained fruits.

title: squash relish
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and place in covered container overnight in refrigerator.
Next day, drain off liquid and add next 5 ingredients.
Bring this mixture to boil, then lower heat and cook for 30 minutes.
Fill sterilized jars and seal.

title: egg fried rice
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add garlic and cook until soft.
Stir in onions and cool for 2 minutes.
Add rice, pork or shrimp and soy sauce.
Stir and cook for 3 minutes. Add remaining ingredients and cook until heated thoroughly. Serves 6 (1 cup per serving).

title: snicker ice cream dessert
directions: In a large (9 x 13 or larger) dish, layer all of the above ingredients beginning with the ice cream sandwiches and finishing with the Magic Shell. Put in freezer overnight and enjoy.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Layer bread, cheese and chopped sausage in a rectangular casserole dish and then repeat.
Mix eggs, milk and mustard together.
Pour over top with mushrooms.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: festive fruit cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Put in bowl.
Drop ini shortening and applesauce.
Beat 2 minutes at low speed.
Add eggs; beat 2 minutes.
Add fruit and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in tube pan (greased) at 350° for 1 hour or less.
Try to see if done, if not leave it longer.

title: ham casserole
directions: Mix all together and put in dish except put 1/2 cup of cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tomato pudding
directions: Melt butter, pour over bread cubes and toss.
Heat tomato puree with water, salt and brown sugar.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Pour mixture over bread cubes and toss.
Put in casserole dish and bake, covered, for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: barbecue sauce and pork ribs
directions: Combine all ingredients (except ribs, salt and pepper); mix thoroughly.
Season pork ribs with salt and pepper to taste. Spread ribs on rack in roasting pan.
Pour sauce over ribs, covering completely.
Turn and baste.
Cook in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: eclair dessert
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line with crackers, trimming to fit with a knife.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Layer 3:
Mix and refrigerate for 1 hour or until slightly congealed.
Spread jello over cheese.
Mix and refrigerate until set.

title: red, white and blue jello salad(wonderful for 4th of july)
directions: Start with cherry jello; dissolve in 1 cup boiling water. Cool in long Pyrex or see-through dish.
Put can of crushed pineapple on top.
Chill until firm, but slightly sticky on top.

title: coconut bread
directions: Grate coconut.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add vanilla.
Add coconut.
Add dry ingredients with 2 parts milk.
Knead 5 minutes.
Cover; let double in size.
Shape and place in greased pan.
Let double in size.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.
Remove from pan; cool on rack.

title: watergate salad
directions: Put pudding in bowl and add pineapple and juice.
Stir well. Add other ingredients.

title: butterscotch sauce(for sundae or over cake)
directions: Mix all the ingredients in a pot.
Cook on medium heat until it boils hard.
Continue boiling 5 more minutes, mixing on and off.
Let the mixture cool.
This sauce is excellent over cake or use for caramel sundae.
This sauce can be kept a long time in the fridge.

title: lamb chop casserole
directions: Prepare soup if using a packet.
Wash rice and put in bottom of a large casserole dish.
Brown chops, if desired, in frying pan and put on top of rice.
Cover with chopped onion.
Pour tomato soup over and sprinkle with thyme.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350° (gas on 6).
Remove lid, top with breadcrumbs and grated cheese; bake for a further 30 minutes until top is golden brown and bubbly.
Serve with salad or green vegetables.
Serves 4.

title: party shrimp
directions: Melt the butter in a pan, but do not let it brown.
Mix in the garlic salt.
Add the shrimp and cook, stirring, over medium heat for about 8 minutes, until the shrimp begin to turn pink.
Do not overcook.
Add the Worcestershire sauce.
Stir to mix.
Turn off the heat; cover and let sit for 4 to 5 minutes.
Sprinkle on the parsley.
Pierce each shrimp with a toothpick or place the shrimp in a serving dish with toothpicks alongside so guests can help themselves.
Serve warm or cold.
Serves 8.

title: casserole hamburger oyster
directions: Fry the hamburger loosely until it is all browned, turning with a spatula during frying so that it is not broken up too much.
Then add the drained oysters and continue frying until the outer edges curl, about 5 minutes.
Set aside and mix the liquid from the oysters with the bread crumbs, parsley and onion.
Season with the salt and pepper.
Add to the browned meat and oysters, tossing lightly to mix.
Put into a well-greased casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Before removing from oven, slip under the broiler for a few seconds so the top can brown.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer until ready to serve.

title: easy fish dinner
directions: Stack one of each ingredient in piece of foil large enough to wrap and seal.
Pepper to taste.
Wrap and place on grill for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: almond fudge shortbread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a mixer bowl beat butter, sugar and salt until fluffy.
Mix in flour.
With floured hands, press into pan.
Bake 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
In a heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt chocolate chips with sweetened condensed milk, stirring constantly until melted. Stir in almond extract.
Spread over shortbread.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Press down firmly and refrigerate.
Cut into bars and store at room temperature.

title: homemade barbecues
directions: Put pork loin, soups, salt and pepper in a crock-pot.
Simmer 12 to 14 hours on High or when pork loin starts falling apart. When this has happened, drain off all juice from crock-pot.
Add barbecue sauce and simmer about 2 hours.
Top this delicious barbecue with cole slaw.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. To hamburger, add onions, chilies and taco seasoning. Let simmer according to seasoning instructions. While hamburger simmers, mix cream of chicken soup and sour cream. Warm this. Pour half of sour cream mixture into bottom of lasagna or cake pan. Roll hamburger into flour shells and place on sour cream mixture. Pour the rest of the sour cream mixture over shells and cover evenly. Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix batter, adding zucchini, raisins and nuts at the end. Put into 2 greased loaf tins.

title: split pea and basil soup
directions: Wash peas and drain.
Place in crock-pot with 4 quarts water. Salt to taste.
Add remaining ingredients.
This dish will be ready to serve in 2 to 4 hours, depending on the type of crock-pot used.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package and drain.
Combine by hand with remaining ingredients.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: baked rice
directions: Place all ingredients in casserole (allow for doubling).
Bake at 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes, stirring after about 15 minutes.
It should be firm, but not dry.
Serve with beef roast or other meat.
Do not add any salt.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Break crackers coarsely into pie shell.
Combine water, sugar and cream of tartar in pan.
Boil for 15 minutes gently.
Add lemon juice to mixture and cool.
Pour syrup over crackers.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cover with top crust.
Cut slits in top crust and bake at 400° to 425° for 20 to 30 minutes. Serve warm or cold.

title: snapper ala king
directions: Cut the head off as close to the jaw as possible and let it bleed well.
(Tie it with rope by back leg and hang it up.)
Put the whole turtle in scalding water (shell and all) for about 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove turtle and scrub well with a good stiff brush. Pull toenails and cut shell away with a very sharp knife.
Don't forget to get all that white meat from back of shell.
Remove internal organs.
Parboil until meat is tender.
Remove meat and skin it.
Use the broth for stew or soup.

title: layered spaghetti bake
directions: Brown meat with green pepper and onion; drain.	Stir in dressing, tomato sauce,
Parmesan
cheese, oregano and pepper. Cook 2 to 3 minutes
over low heat or until thoroughly heated. Place 1/2 of the spaghetti in 2 quart casserole.
Top with 1/2 of the
meat
mixture	and
cup
Cheddar cheese.	Repeat layers. Bake
in
350° oven.
Bake 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cocktail sausages
directions: Place cocktail sausages or hotdogs in crockpot.
Add equal parts of ketchup and brown sugar in a bowl.
Mix until well blended.
Pour over sausages, stir so all sausages are covered. Cook on low until sausages are hot throughout. Serve with toothpicks if desired.
Also great with store bought meatballs.

title: seafood stuffing
directions: Saute onions, peppers and garlic in 1 stick of margarine. When onions are clear, add crabmeat and shrimp.
Season to taste with red pepper, salt and seafood seasoning.
Saute until it is cooked well.
Pour into bowl.
Add Ritz crackers.
Add enough milk to mixture until moist and smooth.
Use to stuff founder, mushrooms, etc.
Enjoy!

title: polynesian casserole
directions: Saute sausage, onion, celery and pepper.
Drain off grease. Add rice, soup packages and bamboo shoots.
Stir up and bake in dish for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chile pie
directions: Place 2 cups Fritos in a 2-quart baking dish. Arrange chopped onion and half the cheese on top. Warm the chili.
Mix with the cooked ground beef (crumbled).
Pour over onion and cheese. Top with remaining Fritos and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, uncovered.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain well.
Add
corn, salsa, tomato sauce, taco mix and spices.
Simmer 5 to 7 minutes.
Stir frequently.

title: orange hash
directions: Place dry jello, cream cheese and Cool Whip in bowl and beat well.
Add oranges and mix.
Add pecans and stir.
Should you like the consistency to be a little thinner, add juice from oranges. Chill in an 8 x 8-inch pan until firm, about 3 hours.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: peanut butter ball candy
directions: Mix and form into balls.
Chill.
Dip into melted chocolate.

title: pizza bread
directions: Roll bread dough out onto floured surface to 8 x 20-inch sheet.
Layer on toppings.
Roll up like jelly roll and place on a cookie sheet.
Cover with towel and let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: nachos and chili
directions: Layer each ingredient, beginning with cream cheese.
Microwave just until cheese melts.
Serve with nachos.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat together oleo and sugars until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Stir in oats, chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by spoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes at 375°.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: "stuff"
directions: Put meat in bottom of electric skillet or large frypan. Cut up next 4 ingredients and put in layers, starting with the carrots. Spread soups over	vegetables. Start cooking on medium-high and finish on low heat. Cook for 30 minutes or more.

title: texas pizza
directions: Combine flour, cornmeal and 1/2 teaspoon salt in mixing bowl. Cut in shortening thoroughly.
Sprinkle in water, 1 tablespoon at a time, mixing with fork until all flour is moist.
Form dough into ball and press out on a pizza pan; chill for 1 hour.

title: picadillio (mexican meat course)
directions: Heat olive oil in a large, heavy skillet and brown meat.
Add onions and garlic and brown.
Add apples, tomatoes, chiles, raisins, olives, cloves, cinnamon, salt and pepper.
Simmer gently, uncovered, until cooked, about 20 minutes.
Add pineapple. Fry almonds until golden and add.
Cook a few minutes longer. Serves 6.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine butter, the sugars, vanilla and pudding mix in large bowl.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually stir in flour and soda.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cherry congealed salad
directions: Mix jello, hot water and marshmallows.
Let melt in top of double boiler.
Let cool and put in refrigerator until syrupy. Fold in creamed cheese and pineapple.
Beat cream or iced evaporated milk until stiff.
Fold in whipped cream and nuts to jello mixture.
Chill.

title: clete's barbecue sauce
directions: Heat over low heat; do not boil.
Wonderful on grilled meat or oven baked.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Crush Oreos in food processor.
Cream together butter, sugar and cream cheese.
In separate bowl, mix together milk, pudding and whipped topping.
Combine the two mixtures.
Alternate layers of mixture and cookie crumbs in clean flowerpot, starting and ending with cookie crumbs.
Chill or freeze.

title: potato cake
directions: Mix in order listed above.
Notes:
cream sugar and shortening, add spices and baking powder mixed with flour.
Fold in last-egg whites beaten well.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) pans, 20-25 minutes at 350°.

title: herby potatoes
directions: In saucepan, melt margarine.
Add celery.
Cook until tender. Stir in spices.
Cut potatoes into 1/2-inch slices, cutting not quite through.
Place each potato on a piece of foil large enough to wrap potato.
Drizzle about half spice mixture into slits. Insert half slice onion.
Top with remaining spice mixture.
Wrap and grill over hot coals 40 to 45 minutes.

title: mexican tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and chicken or ham until smooth; add chilies and onion.
Put mixture in refrigerator and let set. Have tortillas at room temperature.
Put mixture on tortillas; roll up and put extra stuff on ends.
Chill overnight, then slice.

title: swiss style green beans
directions: Put all ingredients, except Ritz crackers, together and pour into a casserole dish.
Crumble crackers over top and
bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: linda's chicken breasts(also used for pork chops)
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/4 cup juice.
Set pineapple aside.
Place chicken in a large shallow dish.
Combine reserved pineapple juice, soy sauce, oil, onion, garlic and sugar, mixing well.
Pour over chicken, reserving marinade.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix well and spread on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
While pumpkin is cooking, take 2 sheets of aluminum foil, lay on a counter.
Next, lay a dish towel on top of foil and sprinkle 10x sugar on dish towel, enough to cover pumpkin when you
flip the pumpkin from the pan to the towel.
Roll as if a jelly roll (towel and pumpkin together).
Let cool approximately 1 hour.

title: zucchini mock apple pie
directions: Cook zucchini in boiling water 2 minutes; drain well.
Mix other ingredients in and place in a 9-inch pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 12 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dj's quick macaroni casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bring to a near boil.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar, butter and milk to a boil.
Let it boil 5 more minutes, stirring constantly.
Take off of heat and add vanilla, peanut butter chips and Marshmallow Creme.
Stir.
Pour into buttered pans.
Let cool and cut.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Blend with Crisco.
Add milk.
Roll out about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Place in ungreased baking pan, sides touching.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: asparagus pimento and egg casserole
directions: Spread asparagus on bottom of buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole.
Add layer of eggs, then strips of pimento. Pour cream of mushroom soup over the top.
Then sprinkle with cheese and top with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: bob's venison "chicago"(from outdoor life deer hunter's yearbook, 1986)
directions: Prepare noodles according to package instructions, then drain thoroughly.
Brown burger and drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, salt and Worcestershire and simmer on very low heat.

title: sunshine punch
directions: Put Jell-O
and
cup boiling water in blender at low speed until
dissolved.
Add pineapple juice and orange juice concentrate and 1 cup cold water.
Blend until combined.
Pour in punch bowl.
Stir in remaining 4 cups cold water.
Add ice. Float orange slices.

title: savory pot roast
directions: Brown meat.
Remove and place on heavy foil.
Pour sauce over and seal tightly.
Wrap again in foil.
Cook at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
For barbecue, just shred the meat.

title: holiday pound cake (fruit cake)
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and beat thoroughly.
Add dry ingredients (sifted together) to mixture.
Add nut mixture. Pour in 10-inch tube pan and bake at 275° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: quick scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter in pressure cooker.
Add the milk.
Let it heat while you thinly slice raw potatoes.
Put half of potatoes in cooker.
Sprinkle with flour, salt and pepper.
Add rest of potatoes and salt on top.
Cook at 15 pounds pressure for 1 to 3 minutes.
Set aside until pressure is down.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Mix together hamburger, pizza sauce, mushrooms, oregano and garlic salt.
Cook until it boils.
Cook rotini noodles, then drain.
Pour milk over noodles; let sit.
Mix 1/2 hamburger mix with 1/2 noodles, then 1/2 cheese.
Repeat.
Put pepperoni on top. Bake at 350°, covered, for 25 minutes.

title: light mushroom gravy
directions: In a medium saucepan, cook mushrooms and onion in butter until tender, stirring occasionally.
Add beef broth and simmer 5 minutes.
Add cornstarch mixture; cook and stir 1 minute or until thickened and bubbly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chipped beef chicken
directions: Line bottom of a casserole with the chipped beef.
Place chicken breasts on top of the chipped beef.
Cover with soup. Cover and bake at 350° for 3 hours.
Serves 6.

title: tourtiere(meat pie)
directions: Pour oil into very large pot over low heat.
Add all ingredients remaining, except pastry; mix well.
Cook, stirring occasionally, for about 30 minutes, or until most liquid is absorbed but mixture is still very moist.
Let cool.
Line pie plates with pastry.
Add filling; cover with top crust.
Seal and cut slits in top.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Bon appetit!!!

title: creamy chicken noodle soup
directions: In a Dutch oven or large saucepan, cover chicken with water. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer for 40 minutes or until tender.
Remove chicken.
Reserve broth.
Bone and shred chicken. Set aside.
Discard bones and skin.

title: parsley cucumber chips
directions: Cut cukes into	1/4-inch
slices and combine with salt. Add enough cold water to cover and let stand overnight.
Drain well.

title: curried lentils and rice
directions: Saute rice, onion and garlic in oil until sizzling.
Add curry and water, then lentils.
Cover and simmer about 30 minutes.
Stir in chopped raw spinach.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: carrots amandine
directions: In a saucepan, cook carrots in 1-inch boiling water with sugar and salt, covered, for 10 to 12 minutes, or until they are tender, but still crisp.
Drain and transfer carrots to a heated dish to keep warm.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix all together and beat several minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
While still warm, punch holes with fork every 1/2-inch and pour glaze over it.

title: apple pickles
directions: Boil all ingredients together, except apples, for 5 minutes. Add apples and cook until tender. Refrigerate or process.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together butter, powdered sugar, vanilla and peanut butter. Form into balls and chill.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin and dip the balls into this mixture.
Chill.

title: chicken chrovale
directions: Mix all ingredients with chicken except cheese and onion rings.
Turn into a 13 x 9-inch pan (large rectangular pan).
Top with cheese and crushed onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: creamy chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender but not brown. Stir in chicken, 1/4 cup of the picante sauce, cream cheese and cumin; heat through. Remove from heat. Stir in 1/2 cup of the shredded cheese. Heat about 1/2 inch oil in small skillet until hot but not smoking. Quickly fry each tortilla in oil to soften, about 2 seconds on each side.

Drain on paper towels. Spoon scant 1/3 cup chicken mixture down center of each tortilla; roll and place seam side down in 12 x 7-inch baking dish. Spoon remaining picante sauce evenly over enchiladas; cover with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° about 15 minutes or until hot. Sprinkle with onion and serve with additional picante sauce. Makes 4 servings.

title: oven crisp chicken and biscuits(biscuits and chicken baked together)
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Melt shortening in oven in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix Bisquick and seasonings in paper bag.
Shake pieces of chicken to coat thoroughly.
Lay chicken skin side down in single layer in hot shortening.
Bake 45 minutes.
Make biscuits (out of Bisquick).
Turn chicken and push to one side in pan.
Set biscuits in single layer on other side.
Bake 15 minutes (until lightly brown and chicken tender).

title: *lemon freeze
directions: Set jello as usual.
When it begins to jell, beat thoroughly. Add juice and rind of lemon.
Whip milk; add sugar as whipped. Combine the two.
Put half of rolled vanilla wafers in bottom of 9 x 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Add mixture.
Put remaining rolled crumbs on top.

title: mock pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in oven for 1 hour.

title: company broccoli
directions: Melt stick of butter in 2-quart casserole. Add 1/2 crackers, finely crushed. Add cubed cheese. Add cooked and drained broccoli. Top with remaining half crackers. Cover and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: super beef stroganoff
directions: Brown pork chops and place in a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Cover with sliced onions and apple slices.
Pour apple cider over all.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: cream cheese icing(bake auction)
directions: Cream the cheese and oleo.
Add 1 cup sugar and vanilla.
Add remainder of sugar.
If too stiff, add milk to reach a spreading consistency, adding a teaspoon at a time.
Delicious on Banana Cake.

title: raw-apple cake
directions: Mix all together, then put into tube pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: quick mexican casserole
directions: In medium skillet, brown ground beef with green onions.
Stir in chilies, tomato soup, salsa, corn, olives, worcestershire sauce, chili powder and garlic powder until well blended.
Place in 2 quart casserole dish. Top with cheese, then evenly spread corn muffin cubes over cheese.
Bake at 350° for
10 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve with sour cream.

title: pasta with tomatoes and basil
directions: *Instead of fresh basil, you can use 3/5 cup chopped Italian parsley plus 3 tablespoons dried basil.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Put sugars, milk, chocolate and syrup in saucepan.
Cook to form soft ball.
Remove from heat.
Add butter; don't stir.
Cool and beat.
Pour into a buttered pan.

title: pineapple frozen surprise
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze.
Serve slightly thawed.

title: fruit cake
directions: Add enough flour to mix well.
Cook at 375° until done.
Put Musketeers bars between layers while hot.
Make Seven Minute Frosting.
Decorate with candy, nuts, cherries, raisins and pineapple.

title: quick rhubarb cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according
to directions.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan.
Dice up rhubarb and carefully put over the top of cake in pan.
Sprinkle sugar over top of rhubarb.
Do not mix or stir.
Carefully pour whipping cream (unwhipped) over rhubarb-sugar mixture; do not stir.
Bake at 350°
or 30 to 40 minutes until done.
Can be served with or without cream. Delicious.

title: monkey bread
directions: Place sugar and cinnamon in bag and mix well.
Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Drop into bag and coat well.
Spray tube pan and drop biscuit pieces into pan.
Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.
Melt 1 stick margarine and 1 cup brown sugar.
Almost let come to a boil.
Pour over biscuit pieces and bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Let stand in pan for 5 minutes after removing from oven.

title: creamy low-fat potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in medium saucepan of boiling salted water until tender, about 25 minutes. Drain and cool.
Cut potatoes into squares.
Whisk yogurt, mustard and tarragon in large bowl until blended.
Add potatoes, bell pepper, green onions and celery; toss.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover and chill well, about 3 hours (can be prepared one day ahead).

title: lemon-lime pizzazz
directions: In blender container combine all ingredients;
process until smooth.
Pour into chilled glasses.
Serve immediately.
Yield:
4 (3/4 cup) servings.

title: love cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
As soon as it is out of the oven, poke holes in cake with toothpick and widen a little with toothpick.
Pour condensed milk over cake, then caramel, then chocolate syrup to your desired consistency.
When completely cooled, spread with Cool Whip on top of cake.
It's delicious.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients. Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: cheese crisps
directions: Grate cheese fine; add butter, red pepper, flour and Rice Krispies.
Mix well.
Roll dough into small balls about the size of a cherry.
Place on cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.
May be frozen.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Saute onions in melted butter until clear, but not brown.
In casserole, sprayed with Pam, make layer of onions, crackers and cheese and end up with crackers.
Spoon 3 to 5 spoons of milk on top to help not be so dry.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes. (This may be doubled but do not use as much cracker crumbs).

title: stuffed shells
directions: Season meat with garlic powder while browning.
Cook shells until almost done.
Dice Mozzarella cheese; dice bread into squares and add milk and egg together with cheese and bread.
Mix meat with cheese/bread mixture.
Stuff shells.
Pour a little sauce on bottom of pan.
Layer shells side by side (mixture side up).
Add remaining sauce and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cabbage soup
directions: In a large stew pot brown meat in drippings.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and cook 2 hours, adding water, if necessary.

title: sugar-free pumpkin custard
directions: Combine milk, eggs, sweetener, vanilla, cinnamon and salt in a bowl.
Mix well.
Stir in pumpkin.
Pour into custard cups.
Bake at 350°
for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: nacho dip-layer
directions: Layer each item, starting with sour cream.

title: 4-kid ice cream sandwiches
directions: Kid No. 1:
Arrange graham crackers on a large cookie sheet.

title: chili sauce
directions: Skin tomatoes and combine with other ingredients.
Boil for about 3 hours.
Stir to keep from sticking.
Add red pepper pod, if desired.
Pour into sterilized jars while hot and seal.
Yield: Approximately 6 pints.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add strawberries, pineapple, nuts and bananas.
Mix well.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into 13 x 9-inch pan or dish and refrigerate.
Chill until firm, then spread Cool Whip on top.
Pour on top remaining half of mixture.
Refrigerate until firm and ready to serve.
Can be used as dessert.

title: chili con queso
directions: Saute garlic and onions in 1 tablespoon of salad oil.
Add green chilies, chopped garlic and onions.
In the meantime, over a double boiler, melt the two cheeses.
When cheese is melted, add sauteed ingredients.
Add seasonings and tomato juice.
Add splashes of Tabasco sauce.

title: brownie pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour mixture into 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: catfish stew
directions: Fry fatback until brown.
Stir in onions and cook until done. Add catsup, tomato soup, Texas Pete, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil over medium heat.
Add catfish.
Cook about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally to keep from sticking to bottom of pan.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Peel apples and cut in small pieces.
Place apples in large bowl and pour lemon juice over them, stirring to mix well.
In a small bowl mix flour, sugar and cinnamon. Combine the apples and dry ingredients, mixing well.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.

title: cold spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; cool.
Add the rest of the ingredients and toss (should set at least 12 hours in the refrigerator).

title: easy quiche
directions: Place meat in bottom of pie shell.
Spread evenly.
Beat together all other ingredients.
Pour over meat.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Rub ribs with cut side of clove of garlic.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Roast, uncovered, 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Run cold water over macaroni to get them cold.
In large bowl, put macaroni and mayonnaise.
Stir until macaroni is completely covered.
Add carrots (may be cut in circles, shredded with a potato peeler or diced), celery, green pepper, tomato and cucumber.
Mix well.
(You can add more or less Miracle Whip to your liking.)
Likewise with the vegetables.

title: mexi-beef bites
directions: Cook and stir beef in large skillet over medium-high heat until beef loses pink color.
Pour off drippings.
Stir cheese, chiles, taco sauce and eggs.
Transfer mixture to 8 x 8-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean and top is golden brown.
Cool in pan 15 minutes. Cut into 36 squares.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes 36 appetizers.

title: beef stroganoff(serves 6)
directions: Cut steak into thin strips.
Coat with flour, salt and pepper. Brown quickly in oil.
Add onions and mushrooms.
Saute over low heat until lightly browned.
Add Worcestershire sauce, soup and sour cream.
Bring to boil.
Add salt, pimento and rice to bouillon.

title: country breakfast pie
directions: Cook sausage until done.
Drain, then crumble.
Make a 1 crust, uncooked, 9-inch pie shell.
Mix cheese and sausage. Sprinkle them into the shell.
Lightly beat eggs in bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Pour into shell. Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool on wire rack 10 minutes. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: eternal meringue
directions: Bring cornstarch and water to a boil or until really thick and clear.
Set aside to cool completely.
Beat 3 egg whites until real stiff; add 3 tablespoons sugar.
Beat 1 minute.
Add cooled cornstarch and beat 2 to 3 minutes more.
Put on pie.
Bake 15 minutes at 350° until golden brown.
Will not fall or water.

title: tea cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Cream sugar and shortening together until fluffy.
Beat eggs and add to sugar and shortening. Mix together well.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Take small amounts of cookie dough and place on floured pastry board.
Roll to 1/4-inch thickness and use cookie cutters to cut out.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cookie should be set, but not brown to be done.
Great for Christmas time to decorate.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Mix butter and flour together by hand. Add grated cheese, then Rice Krispies.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Put on a greased cookie sheet and mash to flatten.
Cook 10 minutes at 425°.
For a different taste, sprinkle with red pepper before baking.
Will keep a long time in tightly covered container.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Cover bottom of rectangular casserole dish with rice.
(Do not use Minute rice.)
Mix soup and water; pour over rice.
Brown pork chops and place over rice.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake, uncovered, in oven for 1 hour at 300°.
Add additional water, if needed.

title: company vegetable casserole
directions: Place frozen vegetables in 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle rice over vegetables.
Set aside.
Combine soup, cheese, onion, salt and milk.
Heat in microwave until cheese melts.
Stir occasionally.
Pour cheese sauce over vegetables.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 1 hour or microwave on High for 15 to 20 minutes. Top with 1 can (2.8 ounces) Durkee French fried onions (optional).

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thaw pie crusts.
Cut chicken to 1/2-inch pieces, salt and pepper and fry in skillet in 2 tablespoons oil.
While chicken cooks, mix Veg-All, mushrooms, chicken soup and 1/2 can water, then add cooked chicken and mix well.
Pour into pie crust.
Top with other pie crust. Cut slits in top and bake on a cookie sheet at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: low-fat banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding, milk and sour cream together.
Add Cool Whip. Layer with bananas and wafers.
Chill and enjoy!

title: hominy au gratin
directions: Melt butter and saute onions and tops for 3 minutes.
Add hominy and heat until warm.
Add sour cream, chilies, pepper and salt; heat until bubbly.
Stir in parsley.
Top with cheese. Broil until cheese melts.

title: raisin meringue pie
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar, salt and spices.
Add egg yolks. Mix well.
Add sour cream, raisins and lemon juice.
Cook over hot water until thick, stirring constantly.
Partially cool.
Add nuts.
Pour into baked shell.
Cool.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add 1/4 cup sugar and cream of tartar gradually. Continue beating until mixture is stiff and glossy.
Spread over pie, sealing edge of pastry.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned, 12 to 15 minutes.

title: wilma's pumpkin roll
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Beat egg on high for 3 minutes.
Beat in sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice. In another bowl, stir in flour, baking powder, pumpkin spice and salt.
Fold this mixture into the pumpkin mixture.
Spread into greased cookie sheet.
Spread with chopped nuts.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Put powdered sugar on kitchen towel.
Put cake on powdered towel and roll up until cool.

title: foamy cream sauce
directions: Beat egg white with salt until stiff.
Beat in sugar gradually.
Add egg yolk and beat until thick.
Fold in whipped cream and vanilla flavoring.
Serve soon after making.

title: glazed pork chops
directions: Arrange pork chops in a flat baking dish.
Combine other ingredients and spread over chops.
Bake, uncovered, for one hour at 250°.
Turn chops and raise heat to 350° and bake another 15 minutes.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Grease and flour 3 (8-inch) cake pans.
Mix all ingredients except egg whites, which are folded in last.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Heat milk
to
boiling	point.	Add celery and let cook about 3 to 5 minutes until tender, but not mushy.
Add oysters until they
curl.
Then
crush
saltines with fingers, not too fine. Add
butter
and
grated cheese.
Salt and pepper.	Let cheese melt
slowly,
do
not stir.
When oysters curl, reduce heat to low until cheese melts.
Serve while hot.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Mix together and pour in casserole.
Cover ingredients with sliced American cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Combine corn flakes, Parmesan, salt and pepper.
Stir and set aside.
Peel eggplant.
Cut into slices.
Dip each piece into egg and then coat with crumb mixture. Arrange in buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Turn slices over and bake 15 more minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients except Mozzarella cheese in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over eggplant.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: horse cookies(for horses)
directions: Mix ingredients.
Roll into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet and flatten.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, or until golden brown.
Do not eat!

title: salmon patties
directions: Beat eggs in medium bowl.
Add 1/2 cup corn flake crumbs, salmon, salt, pepper, onion and milk.
Mix well; shape in 12 patties, about 2 inches.
Coat with rest of crumbs.
Fry in small amount of oil in large skillet for about 2 minutes on each side, until browned.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: muffins
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
Combine the flour, baking powder and salt.
In a separate bowl, cream the butter or margarine with the sugar until light and fluffy.
Add the eggs and beat well. Blend this mixture with the dry ingredients alternately with the milk.
Fold the fruit and nuts (etc.) in quickly.

Because these muffins will rise up and over the edge of your muffin tin, you'll want to grease the top of the pan as well as the cups. Fill the cups nearly 3/4 full and sprinkle with the spiced sugar.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mini-cheesecakes
directions: Place vanilla wafers in paper baking cups (cupcake size).
Mix other ingredients.
Pour mixture over wafers.
Fill 3/4 full. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool and top with pie filling.

title: cocoons
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add flour, vanilla and nuts. Shape in balls or finger-size shapes and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 50 to 60 cookies.

title: potato pleasers(great for a crowd!)
directions: Brown bacon, onion and bell pepper.
Slice potatoes (I leave the skins on) in 1/4-inch slices into a buttered casserole dish. Cover with bacon mixture.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°. Remove cover.
Add grated cheese and return to oven until melted. Top with dollops of sour cream and serve.

title: buffalo chicken dip
directions: Beat cream cheese and ranch dip.
Fold in chicken and celery. Add buffalo sauce to taste.

title: pear relish
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar, salt and celery seed in a 5-quart kettle. Bring to a boil. Add pears, onion and peppers.
Bring to a boil. Simmer, uncovered, 40 minutes.
Ladle into jars and seal.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all the ingredients; mix well.
Let harden in refrigerator.
Form into 2 balls.
Roll in nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: hearty vegetable chowder
directions: Combine chicken broth and water in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Add mixed vegetables.
Cook 15 minutes until tender. Saute onion and pepper in Dutch oven until tender.
Blend in flour, paprika and mustard.
