Gradually add milk, vegetables and broth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese and pepper.
Stir until cheese melts.
Yield: 7 cups.

title: cheese chili cubes
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat egg with electric mixer until light. Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to eggs and mix well.
Fold in Monterey Jack cheese, cottage cheese and chilies. Turn into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven, let stand 10 minutes.
Cut in small squares.
Serve hot.
(3 to 4 dozen appetizers)

title: french coconut pie(it's perfect)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 2 unbaked 9-inch pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pies or 18 tarts.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake as directed on box.

title: crab mold
directions: Soften gelatine in cold water.
Sprinkle lemon juice over shrimp and crabmeat.
Melt cream cheese and soup in double boiler. Add gelatine and mayonnaise.

title: easy hershey pie
directions: Melt Hershey bar in double boiler.
Remove from heat.
Pour Cool Whip into chocolate.
Pour mixture into pie crust.
Chill until firm.
Top with shaved chocolate, if desired.

title: apricot cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in an 8 x 8-inch pan for 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool cake completely before icing.

title: oatmeal rocks
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture along with milk.
Add oatmeal.
Stir until completely blended.
Stir in chips and nuts, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Bake pie shells; follow directions on package.
Wash and cap strawberries; set aside.
Boil 2 cups water, 2 cups sugar and 4 tablespoons cornstarch until thick.
Add jello; set aside for later.
Mix cream cheese, milk, and sugar until creamy.
Then fold in Cool Whip.
Pour cream cheese mixture into baked pie shells. Then add strawberries.
Top with jello mixture; chill.

title: green chili soup
directions: Mix and heat the first four ingredients.
Crush Doritos and cut Monterey Jack cheese into bowls.
Pour hot soup over Doritos and cheese.

title: microwave pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Place butter in round glass 8 or 9-inch
microwave safe dish. Microwave on High power for 35 seconds.
Sprinkle brown sugar over butter.
Arrange pineapple slices on top and place cherries in center of pineapple ring; set aside.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions using pineapple juice as part of the liquid required.
Spread cake batter over pineapple slices, brown sugar and cherries which have been arranged in glass dish.
Microwave on 50% power 5 minutes.
Turn.
Microwave 2 to 3 minutes on High.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Turn onto plate.
Yields 5 to 6 servings.

title: beet pickles
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients and pour over beets that have been put in jars.
Process 30 minutes in water bath.
Yields 7 pints.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: In small bowl with mixer at low speed, beat butter, 1 1/4 cups flour, 1/4 cup sugar and 1 egg yolk until well mixed.
Cover; refrigerate 1 hour.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Make pudding as directed and then fold in Cool Whip.
Frost the graham crackers.
Place a layer of frosted graham crackers on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then add half of the pudding.
Add another layer of frosted graham crackers.
Put another layer of balance of pudding on the graham crackers.
Top this dish with a final layer of frosted graham crackers.
Chill for 24 hours.

title: caramel ribbon brownies
directions: Heat and melt the caramels into the 1/3 can evaporated milk. Mix the chocolate cake mix, melted oleo or butter and remaining 1/3 cup evaporated milk together.
Spread 1/2 mixture in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts over hot baked crust.
Drizzle caramel mixture on top.
Spread rest of cake mixture on that.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes more. Sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add pumpkin, oil and other ingredients; mix well.
Pour into 5 well-greased 1 pound coffee cans, each 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: carrot cream soup
directions: Saute onion and garlic in margarine until tender.
Add broth, carrots, potatoes and seasonings; simmer until vegetables are cooked, about 1 hour.
Put soup through blender until smooth. Reheat before serving and add cream.
Nice with a pat of sour cream or yogurt (plain).
You would never guess it's carrot soup!

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar together, then add other ingredients. Pour into unbaked shells.
Bake at 350° until golden brown. Makes 2 pies.

title: peach conserve
directions: In a large enamel or stainless saucepan, combine sugar, peaches and pineapple including juice.
Bring to a boil; stir and cook to dissolve sugar.
Boil for 20 minutes.
Stir in gelatin.
While mixture is still hot, pour into hot sterile jars.
Seal with hot lids and rings.
Makes 6 to 8 small jars.
Good on toast or biscuits.
Great warmed in microwave and served over vanilla ice cream.

title: pea salad
directions: Heat last 3 ingredients and cook until sugar dissolves.
Pour over vegetables.
Enjoy!

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: In a large skillet, combine all liquid ingredients, including catsup.
Add peach preserves and stir well; add soup mix and garlic and stir again.
Let simmer 10 minutes.
Add chicken and chestnuts.
Serve over rice.

title: stuffed broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain and set aside.
Melt 4 tablespoons butter; add flour and mix.
Add bouillon cubes and milk.
Cook until sauce thickens.
Grease a 2-quart baking dish and place broccoli in it.
Pour over the sauce.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and a pinch of salt. Melt margarine; mix with first ingredients. Add beaten eggs, vanilla and buttermilk. Mix well. Pour in deep 9-inch crust. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine all ingredients (except soup) in order listed.
Mix well.
Form into large patties and roll in flour.
Brown both sides in hot oil.
Pour soup and 1 can of water mix over meat and simmer, covered, for 45 minutes.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, salt and spices.
Do not heat! Mix cucumbers and onions and pack in glass containers.
Pour vinegar mixture over cucumbers and onions.
Cover tightly.
Refrigerate for 5 days before tasting.
Pickles keep in refrigerator for one year or more.

title: nacho meat dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together well, heat and serve as a dip for chips, over chips with a salad, in a burrito with refried beans, over baked potatoes, or your own ideas as appetizer or main meal!

title: breakfast "before"
directions: Brown and drain 1 pound of sausage. Cube 3 slices of bread and put in bottom of greased or sprayed 10 x 14-inch baking dish. Place sausage on top of bread cubes.
Place 1 1/2 cups of grated mild Longhorn cheese on top of sausage.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Drain and chop artichokes.
Stir all ingredients together. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: lemon cake
directions: Combine and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pie crust
directions: With pastry blender cut lard into dry ingredients.
Beat egg, water and vinegar together.
Stir into flour; chill.
This may be frozen in a lump or rolled into crusts and freeze.

title: brown rice pilaf with dates and carrots
directions: In a large heavy saucepan, cook the onion, the carrot and the rice in the oil over moderately low heat, stirring, for 1 minute. Stir in the dates, the rind, the broth, 1/2 cup water and salt and pepper to taste; bring the liquid to a boil and simmer the mixture, covered, for 45 to 50 minutes or until the liquid is absorbed and the rice is tender.
Fluff the pilaf with a fork; transfer it to a serving dish and sprinkle it with the almonds and the scallion greens.
Season with lemon juice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: bacardi rum cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Grease and flour 10 inch or 12-cup Bundt pan. Sprinkle pecans over bottom of pan. In a bowl, combine cake mix

and remaining cake ingredients together until well blended. Pour batter over pecans in cake pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Remove from oven and cool. Invert on a serving plate. Prick top of cake with a fork or cake tester. Drizzle and smooth some of the glaze evenly over top and sides of cake. Allow cake to absorb the glaze, then repeat until all glaze has been used.

title: egyptian eyes
directions: Remove center of bread.
Butter both sides of bread.
Place bread in hot frying pan over medium heat.
Drop egg into hole in bread.
Fry until egg is set, then turn over and cook other side. Makes 1 serving.

title: cream of mushroom meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger, stuffing, milk, and curry powder.
Roll into small balls.
Fry/brown In skillet with 2 tablespoons oil.
Place browned meatballs into crockpot.
Add soup with 1 cup water.
Cook 3 to 4 hours.
Makes about 40 meatballs.

title: lemon blueberry muffins
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda and lemon rind together.
Beat together eggs, margarine and sugar.
Stir in yogurt and dry ingredients.
Fold in blueberries.
Spoon into greased muffin tins and bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: ham and red-eye gravy
directions: Trim excess fat from ham slices. Soak in warm water for 15 minutes; drain. Heat ham fat in skillet over medium heat until melted. Brown ham on both sides over medium heat; remove to warm platter. Pour drippings from skillet. Pour hot coffee into skillet. Stir and scrape ham particles from skillet; pour over baking powder biscuits. Serve with ham. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: skillet okra and vegetables
directions: In a heavy 12-inch skillet cook bacon until crisp.
Remove and drain on paper towel.
Reserve 2 tablespoons of drippings in skillet.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Add the drained vegetables; season with salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer uncovered about 20 minutes or until liquid has almost evaporated. Crumble bacon and sprinkle on top.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
May use frozen okra or fresh okra.

title: cool and care-free lemon fruit freeze
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in sugar.
Add crumbs.
Reserve 1/3 cup for garnish.
Pat crumbs firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 12 minutes; cool.

title: chicken livers
directions: Saute onions and celery in margarine until celery is wilted. Remove and set aside.
Add livers and turn heat high.
Cook, turning once or twice, until done, approximately 3 to 5 minutes. Top with onions and celery.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: corn flakes cookies
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to boil.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter and corn flakes.
Shape into balls with buttered hands.

title: johnny appleseed pudding
directions: Peel and slice apples in buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons sugar mixed with cinnamon.
Mix flour, baking
powder and salt.
Combine 3/4 cup sugar, milk, melted butter or margarine.
Combine dry ingredients with milk mixture and pour over apples.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with whipped cream or custard sauce.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix both sausage and ground meat together.
Mix remaining ingredients together and place in greased pan.
Cover with catsup and bake in oven at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6 people. (Save a few chips to sprinkle over top of casserole.)

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Boil together butter, cocoa and milk.
Add sugar and vanilla. Mix until good consistency.

title: white bread
directions: Grease pans.
Beat with electric mixer.
Add next 3 cups flour.
Mix and place on board.
Let rest 6 minutes.
Punch down 10 minutes.
Divide in 2 loaves.
Put in pans.
Let rise 1 hour. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Top with 1/2 pint sour cream (optional).

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Mix soup and milk together.
Add everything else together, except crackers and 1/2 cup cheese.
Put into rectangular glass dish.
Sprinkle cheese and crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or microwave, covered with plastic wrap, one corner vented, for 6 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken and stuffing
directions: Mix stuffing as directed.
Mix soup with milk or sour cream. Add cut up chicken to soup mix and place in 13 x 9 pan.
Top with stuffing mix.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: caramel pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Then add milk.
Beat well.	Add egg yolks (save whites), vanilla and butter.
Mix well.
Put 1/4 cup of sugar in skillet on stove eye and brown.
Warm the milk mixture and add to the brown sugar mixture.
Cook on top of stove until thickened.
Cool, then pour into already baked pie crust. Beat the 3 egg whites until stiff.	Gradually add 6 tablespoons of sugar and beat well.
Spoon over pie and brown in oven.

title: peanut butter and bacon spread
directions: Puree peanuts. Add finely crumbled bacon. Makes 1 cup.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Combine crust ingredients.
Press into the bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan; chill.

title: great south bay clam pie
directions: Scrub and steam open clams.
Chop clams.
Partially fry bacon and cut up.
Slice onion and potatoes and partially cook (about 10 minutes).
Melt butter.
Add flour, milk and clam juice, stir until thick.
Combine all ingredients in baking dish.
Make pie crust, roll out thick and place over dish.
Bake in hot oven (425°) until bubbly and crust is slightly browned, about 1/2 hour.
Yields about 6 servings.

title: hot shrimp dip
directions: Cook mushrooms in butter until lightly browned.
Stir in cottage cheese, sour cream, salad dressing, salt, garlic salt and soy sauce.
Heat over low heat until hot.
Add shrimp and heat. Serve with bread sticks, rye wafers and Melba toast rounds.

title: dave's favorite potato soup
directions: Put all ingredients into large pot.
Heat until boiling, stirring occasionally.
Simmer until vegetables are soft.

title: applesauce pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 2 pie shells.
Bake until done.

title: banana crush
directions: Bring the sugar and water to a boil for 5 minutes. Cool completely.

title: crazy cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: seafood mousse
directions: Soften the gelatin in the water; dissolve over hot water, stirring constantly.
Over low heat, beat together the tomato soup and cream cheese until smooth and hot; turn off heat.
Stir in the gelatin; cool thoroughly.
Stir in the remaining ingredients. Turn into a 4 to 5 cup mold; chill until firm.
Unmold and serve with party-style (small slices) rye bread.

title: orange roll dough
directions: Scald milk.
Add shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast.
Let stand 5 minutes for yeast to rise.
Add beaten eggs, orange juice and rind.
Beat thoroughly.
Add flour slowly and work in well.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: moose pot roast
directions: Dice onion into 1/2-inch pieces.
Cut carrot into 1/2-inch slices.
Cut celery in 1/2-inch pieces.
Canned beef broth can be substituted.
One teaspoon dry thyme can also be substituted. Preheat oven to 175°.
In a heavy Dutch oven or thick roasting pan, heat oil over medium-high heat until it shimmers.
Add roast to pan and brown well on all sides.
When brown all over, remove and immediately add onion, carrot and celery to pan.
Reduce heat slightly and continue to cook until they become caramelized in appearance.
Add meat back to pan.
Add tomato paste, stock, bay leaf, thyme, peppercorns and garlic.
Heat liquid until it begins to steam, no hotter.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups sugar in well beaten egg yolks.
Add flour, salt and 1/2 cup water in mixing bowl.
Convert to cooking pan and remaining water.
Cook on low heat or in double boiler.
Cook until it thickens.
Add lemon juice and grated lemon rind.
Cool slightly and pour mixture into pie shell.

title: apricot jam
directions: Use dried apricots.
Heat them in a little water and simmer until tender.
Mash and measure 4 cups pulp.
Cut apricots, sugar and lemon juice in a saucepan.
Add a tiny pinch of salt; stir until sugar is dissolved over low heat.
Increase heat and bring to a boil, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Pour into hot jelly glasses; cool and seal.
Fills 6 (6 ounce) glasses.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Blend ingredients together in bowl.
Can be done by hand. Pour into 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cheese scalloped potatoes
directions: Put sliced potatoes equally on four squares of heavy-duty foil. Top with soup and Cheddar.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Or place on grill, turning once.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Drain juice from fruit and add water to juice to make 2 cups. Heat.
Pour one-half of this over Jello.
Dissolve cream cheese and marshmallows in the other one-half of juice/water mixture and add to the Jello.
Place in refrigerator and congeal partially.
Add whipped cream and fold in fruit.
Chill until firm.

title: yogurt pancakes
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and baking soda; set aside.
Beat egg lightly and add milk; stir into dry ingredients. Stir in yogurt.
Yields about 10 pancakes.

title: zucchini creole
directions: Tomatoes should be peeled and diced if using fresh ones.
Add all ingredients, except squash, to butter and cook 5 minutes. Cube the large squash and put in a baking dish.
Pour tomato mixture over squash.
Cover with grated cheese and bread crumbs. Sprinkle with water and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: country-french chicken
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, melt butter.
Add chicken pieces skin side down and brown well.
Using tongs, turn chicken pieces until all sides are brown.
Place all pieces of chicken in a large baking dish and set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Add onions, carrots and garlic to skillet drippings.
Saute over medium heat until onions and carrots are lightly browned.
Add brandy to skillet.
Carefully ignite brandy and shake skillet until the flames subside.
Add wine, parsley, bay leaf, salt, pepper, thyme and ground cloves.
Turn up heat to high and bring carrot mixture to boiling, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat. Put carrot mixture into baking dish.
Cover baking dish with lid or foil and place on center rack of oven.
Bake for 30 minutes. Uncover dish and place sugar snap peas evenly over chicken and carrot mixture.
Cover baking dish and bake 30 minutes or until juices run clear when chicken is pierced with a fork and vegetables are tender.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve on a decorative platter.
Serves 4.
Suggestions:
Serve with boiled potatoes, French bread and wine.

title: never fail pie pastry
directions: Put flour, salt and lard in large bowl (electric mixer). Blend well on low speed.
Combine egg, water and vinegar.
Stir into flour mixture.
Gather up dough with hands.
Wrap in waxed paper or Saran Wrap.
Chill for easier handling.

title: creamy chicken enchiladas
directions: Melt butter in large skillet over medium heat.
Add onions and saute for 5 minutes.
Add chiles; saute 1 minute.
Stir in cream cheese (low fat can be used) and chopped chicken.
Stir constantly until cream cheese melts.
Spoon 2-3 tablespoons of mixture down center of each tortilla.
Roll up tortillas and place seam side down in lightly greased 13x9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with Monterey Jack cheese and drizzle half and half over all. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 5-6.

title: tri-bean bake
directions: In
a
large skillet fry bacon and onion until bacon is crisp; drain
off
fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Make a well.
Add oil, pumpkin and water.
Blend well with beater.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well each time.
Fold in nuts.
Pour batter into 2 or 3 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: crescent chicken salad buns
directions: Separate rolls into 8 squares.
Place mixture in center of rolls.
Pull corners together to seal mixture inside and make a ball.
Dip in margarine.
Place, sealed side down, on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: faye's crock-pot chicken and dressing
directions: Boil chicken breast until done, reserving the liquid.
Shred chicken after it has cooled.
Crumble and mix cornbread and biscuits together.
To the cornbread mixture add the following and mix well:

1 can of soup, celery, onion, boiled eggs, sage or poultry seasoning, salt and pepper to taste and enough of the reserved liquid to make a very moist consistency but not runny. Add 1/2 of the second can of soup to the crock-pot.
On top of that, add 1/2 of the cornbread mixture.
Add 1/2 of the shredded chicken to the top of the cornbread mixture.
Then add the remaining half of the cornbread mixture.
Add remaining chicken. Cover chicken with remaining half of the soup.
Set crock-pot on low and cook for 3 to 3 1/2 hours.
Serve hot.
Makes about 8 to 10 servings.

title: butter squares
directions: Beat the cake mix, 1 egg and butter together.
Stir in pecans. Press on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Be sure whites are at room temperature.
Gradually add sugar.
Continue beating until stiff. Add salt and vanilla; mix well.
Add nuts and chocolate chips (I use mini chips).
Preheat oven to 350°.
Drop mixture by teaspoon onto a foil-covered sheet.
Place into oven and immediately turn oven off.
Leave cookies in closed oven overnight.
Store in an airtight container.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: beef and bean enchiladas
directions: Prepare beef and add refried beans and seasoning.
Mix well. Put this in shells and roll up.
Place in greased casserole dish. Put rice over top.
Mix enchilada sauce with can of water and pour over rice.
Top with cheese and onion.
Put in 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: spinach stuffing
directions: Put first 8 ingredients in blender and blend until it's liquid. Combine broken bread, spinach and blender ingredients in a large bowl; mix.
Bake in 2-quart casserole 1 hour at 300°.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: my mother's butter chiffon pound cake
directions: Cream butter and 1 cup sugar thoroughly.
Add beaten egg yolks, then flour sifted with baking powder.
Beat egg whites, gradually beat into them 3/4 cup sugar and beat until stiff.
Combine two mixtures.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for about 50 minutes.
Cool in pan.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Peel and grate potatoes and onion into milk. Mix with remaining ingredients, except fat. Drop by tablespoons into hot fat in skillet. Brown on both sides and serve at once.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter cocoa bon-bons
directions: Beat
cream
cheese
and
milk;
blend in confectioners sugar, cocoa and vanilla.
Stir in nuts.	Chill about 1 hour. Shape into
inch
balls,
place on wax paper lined tray. Chill uncovered
or
4 hours or overnight.
Stir in peanut butter chips
and	oil
in
top of double boiler over hot, not boiling water until melted.
Dip each ball.
Chill.
Store in cool place. Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: banana pickles
directions: Peel large pickles and pack in jars.
Heat remaining ingredients and pour over pickles in jars.
Seal and cold pack 10 minutes.

title: leona's strawberry pie
directions: Combine marshmallows and milk in a non-stick saucepan. Cook until smooth. Puree strawberries in food processor. Fold in whipped topping. Stir all together. Pour in pie crust. Refrigerate.

title: stroganoff casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Butter shallow 2.5-quart casserole and set aside. Melt butter in large heavy skillet over moderately high heat. Add beef, mushrooms, onions, garlic, marjoram and thyme. Cook, stirring and breaking up chunks of meat about 10 minutes. Reduce heat to low; add tomato sauce. Cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes. Add all remaining ingredients except noodles and cheese. Cook, stirring until cream cheese melts. Fold in noodles. Turn into casserole dish, spreading evenly and top with cheese. Bake, uncovered, until bubbly and tipped brown, about 20 minutes.

title: spicy apricot cake
directions: Beat sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add baby food, one jar at a time.
Add flour, half of it with remaining ingredients, then beat in the remainder.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a greased, floured tube or Bundt pan.
Cool right side up a little while before turning over.
Sprinkle with sifted confectioners sugar.
(Stays moist for several days.)

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all together and roll in small balls.
Bake at 400° until lightly brown.
These may be frozen.
Cook as many as desired. Makes 70 small balls.

title: family size chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Defrost peas and carrots and then drain. Add next 3 ingredients and pour into a buttered 3-quart baking dish. Mix flour and milk together and pour over top of dish. Dot with butter. Bake in preheated oven for 1 hour. Serves 6 to 8.

title: tomato bake
directions: Line bottom of a 10-inch pie pan (not sides) with biscuits. Press them to make a solid crust.
Cover crust with tomato slices. Sprinkle with green onions, basil, salt and pepper.
Combine mayonnaise and grated cheese; frost tomato pie (going to pan rim). Bake in a preheated 425° oven for 10 to 15 minutes, until top has begun to brown.
Let cool before cutting into wedges to serve. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: crazy chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt, soda and cocoa into bowl. Make well in the middle. Add remaining ingredients. Beat with beater 3 minutes. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: canned vegetable beef soup
directions: Cook stew beef until tender and completely done.
Pour off liquid and use to make 1 quart water.
Tear apart beef in bite size pieces.
Cook butter beans, peas and green beans.
Mix all ingredients well.
You may leave out the vegetables you don't want and add others or more of these.
Keep proportions about the same. Bring everything to a boil.
Place in jars and pressure cook for 20 minutes on 10 pounds pressure.
You may choose to cook for 30 minutes before putting in jars, then boil jars in water bath for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats; add butter, stir and let set for 20 minutes.
Beat in both sugars and eggs.
Add flour, salt, soda, baking powder, cinnamon and vanilla, and lastly the nuts.
Mix all together and bake for 35 minutes at 350° in square pan.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix together and bake in deep casserole for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: fettuccine carbonnara
directions: Season with any or all of the following:
Cracked black pepper, garlic powder, onion powder or basil.

title: cheese-vegetable bake
directions: Slice vegetables into 1-inch pieces.
Cook until crisp-tender and drain well.
Layer with grated cheese in a baking pan.
Bake at 250° about 30 minutes or until cheese melts through.

title: microwave oven meat loaf
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
well.
Make 6 small meat loaves. Put in
glass baking dish.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Cook on High
8 minutes.
Drian off all fat.
Pour one can tomato soup over meat. Cover with plastic wrap; cook 2 minutes.

title: cream cheese pastries
directions: Unroll and spread 1 can of crescent rolls in a jellyroll pan. Mix 1 egg yolk, cream cheese and sugar, spread evenly on top of crescent rolls, unroll second can of crescent rolls and place on top.
Beat 1 egg yolk and brush on the top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: cheesy broccoli dish
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Place in 1 1/2-quart or 2-quart casserole dish.
Cube the cheese and place cubes on top of broccoli. Melt butter in separate pan and pour 1/2 of melted butter over broccoli and cheese.
Place cracker crumbs on top.
Pour remaining butter or margarine over crackers.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until bubbly.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Combine.
Chill for 1/2 hour.
Shape into balls.
Bake for 10 minutes at 325°.

title: hot layered mexican dip
directions: In a 9x13-inch baking dish, layer ingredients as follows: refried beans, sour cream, taco seasoning mix, picante sauce and Cheddar cheese.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 50 minutes in loaf pan.

title: crusty pound cake
directions: Cream butter well in a large mixing bowl; add sugar gradually, mixing until texture is fine and mealy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flavorings.
Combine flour and salt; stir flour mixture into batter, beating until flour is moistened.
Do not overbeat.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes or until a toothpick inserted comes out clean and cake shrinks slightly from sides of pan.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Turn out onto a wire rack to complete cooling.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Sprinkle gelatin on cold water to soften.
Heat V-8 juice. Pour over gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Add vinegar, salt and pepper.
Chill until thick; add celery and pickles.

title: baked chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces and vegetables in bottom of greased baking dish.
Pour soup and milk mixture over.
Bake in a 350° oven until chicken is tender.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Graham Cracker Crust:
Mix crumbs, sugar and melted oleo.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Set in refrigerator for 1/2 hour.

title: clams in batter
directions: Mix clam liquor, milk, salt and pepper together.
Mix and sift flour and baking powder and add to first mixture.
Add beaten eggs.
Put clams in batter and cook 4 to 6 minutes.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Cream margarine and powdered sugar.
Slowly add flour.
Follow with nuts and vanilla.
Shape into small balls and bake 15 to 18 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet at 325°.

title: orange julius
directions: Put in blender. Blend until foamy.

title: toffee
directions: Butter a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Spread pecans in pan. Heat sugar and butter until boiling, stirring constantly, for 7 minutes.
Immediately spread over nuts in pan.
Sprinkle chocolate pieces over hot mixture.
Place baking sheet over pan to contain heat and melt chocolate.
Spread melted chocolate over candy. While hot, cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Chill until firm.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken with salt, pepper, onion and celery seed (season according to your taste). Once chicken is done, set aside the broth and debone chicken. Mix chicken, all can items and salt and pepper to taste. Add some broth a little at

a time so that mixture is creamy. Cook mixture together until all seasonings have blended together. Place crushed chips along the bottom of a casserole dish. Pour mixture on top and cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese has melted.

title: squash dressing casserole
directions: Saute celery, onion and pepper in margarine.
Stir in cornbread, squash and milk.
Add soup; mix well.
Bake in casserole at 350° until browned.

title: peanut butter cookies(grandma batty's recipe)
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add peanut butter, then egg. Sift together flour, soda and salt and gradually add to mixture. Add vanilla.
Form into rolls about 1 1/2-inch diameter.
(May be refrigerated at this point.)
Slice 3/8 to 1/4-inch thick and place slices on baking sheet.
Press down about half way with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: perfect pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar well until very light and fluffy.
Add flavoring.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well. Add alternately the measured flour and baking powder with milk. Pour into prepared tube pan.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Melt together butter and chocolate chips.
Mix with other ingredients.
Pour into buttered Pyrex dish.
Sit in a refrigerator until hard.

title: cajun potatoes
directions: Dice and cook potatoes; drain.
Saute diced onions with paprika.
Add lots of chopped fresh parsley.
Salt and pepper. Toss over cooked potatoes.
Serve hot as side dish.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain and mix all vegetable ingredients together.
Add grated cheese on top of vegetables.
Melt butter; add cracker crumbs and butter together.
Sprinkle over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican tortilla
directions: Layer 1/2 the tortilla chips on bottom of dish.
Combine soups and Ro-Tel tomatoes and pour 1/2 over chips.
Layer 1/2 of meat and cheese on top and continue to layer the rest in the same order.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: quick mexican corn bread
directions: Combine first 3
ingredients.
Add
remaining
ingredients, mixing well.
Pour	into well-greased 8-inch baking pan. Bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden.

title: aunt ethel stayton's chocolate pie filling
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; stir in milk.
Cook over moderate heat until it thickens and boils 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Stir half of mixture into beaten yolks.
Return to mixture and boil 1 minute.
Add butter.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: easy punch
directions: Combine all in large punch bowl with lemon slices and ice cubes; stir and serve.

title: gumbo
directions: Cook the flour and oil in frying pan.
Add the remaining ingredients, adding meat as desired.
Excellent use for leftover fish after filleting, cooking and deboning.

title: caramel corn
directions: Pop enough popcorn for 6 quarts.
Pour preceding ingredients over popped corn.
Bake 1 hour at 250°.
Stir every 20 minutes.

title: world's best cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream the butter and sugars until light and fluffy. Add egg and oil.
Mix well. Add oats, corn flakes, coconut and nuts.
Mix well after each. Add vanilla.
Mix and stir well.
Mix dry ingredients. Add to creamed mixture, mixing well. Form into balls about the size of walnuts.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets. Flatten with fork dipped in water. Bake for 12 minutes. Allow to cool on cookie sheets for a few minutes.
You can sprinkle with sugar while warm.

title: pizza spaghetti
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Add onion and cook until tender. Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour melted butter in 2 1/2-quart dish. Toss cooked spaghetti in melted butter.
Add meat, onion, mushrooms, oregano, salt, tomato paste and water.
Toss with spaghetti.
Top with cheeses.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350° until spaghetti is brown and bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: cornbread dressing and chicken
directions: Boil chicken with chopped onions and celery.
Take bones out. Mix with cornbread and chicken with broth.
Add eggs with salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into baking dish and bake.

title: oven apple pancakes
directions: Beat eggs, milk, salt and flour until smooth.
Let batter rest.
Combine sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over apples and toss to mix.
Butter generously 2 (9-inch) pie pans.
Divide apples between pans.
Stir batter and pour over apples (about 1 cup to each pan).
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until pancakes are golden brown, puffed and set.
Serve with whipped cream or apple syrup.

title: banana cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Add oil and mix until blended. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Grease and fill 4 small loaf pans 3/4 full.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Put the cheese and pimentos through a food grinder (do not use a blender). Then cook in a double boiler the following dressing.

title: beef and pepper kabobs
directions: In a glass bowl or heavy-duty plastic bag, combine lemon juice, oil onion, thyme, salt and pepper.
Add meat;
stir or shake to coat.
Cover or seal and refrigerate six (6) hours or overnight.
Cut peppers into 1-inch squares and thread onto skewers alternately with meat.
Grill over hot coals, turning often, for 12 to 15 minutes or until the meat reaches desired doneness.

title: peanut patties
directions: Boil sugar, Karo, peanuts and milk together to soft ball stage.
The peanuts will crackle and pop.
Add remaining ingredients, cool and beat until it will hold it's shape.
Drop by spoonfuls onto a buttered pan to harden.

title: corned beef stew
directions: Cut onion and brown in hot fat.
Add beans and tomatoes. Simmer 5 minutes.
Break beef into small chunks.
Add to mixture and cook 5 minutes more.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serves 4.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Thoroughly stir together. Cover and refrigerate.
(Make sure spinach is dry.)
When ready to serve, place bread on serving plate.
Fill center with dip and place the bread pieces around the plate to dip with.
Attractive and very good.

title: honey-orange pork chops
directions: In a shallow dish, combine juices, A. 1., honey, pepper and garlic powder.
Add meat, turning to coat.
Cover; marinate in refrigerator for 6 to 24 hours, turning once.

title: grated sweet potato pudding
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs. Add sweet milk and vanilla. Pour over grated sweet potatoes.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into large baking dish.
Bake in hot oven about 450 degrees for 30 minutes, stirring about every 10 minutes.
Lower the temperature to 400 degrees and continue
baking, stirring occasionally, for another thirty minutes, or until thick.
Mixture will rise during early baking and will bubble, then it will cook down.
This will begin to brown along edges and across top.

title: ham and sauerkraut balls
directions: In small skillet, melt butter.
Add onion.
Cook and stir over medium heat until tender.
Stir in 3 tablespoons flour, garlic powder and cayenne.
Cook until mixture thickens, stirring constantly.
Transfer mixture to medium mixing bowl.
Add ham, sauerkraut, cheese, egg and parsley.
Mix thoroughly. Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes.

title: watermelon pie
directions: Stir water into jello in bowl 2 minutes until dissolved.
Mix water and ice to make 1 1/4 cups.
Stir into jello to thicken. Remove any remaining ice.
Stir in whipped topping until smooth. Refrigerate 10 minutes or until mixture will mound.
Spoon into crust.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until firm.
Garnish with additional whipped topping, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: lasagna
directions: Saut olive oil, chopped onions and garlic.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, tomato paste, water, basil, salt and pepper.
Simmer on low heat for 1 hour.
Cook lasagna noodles (drain).
Mix in bowl Ricotta cheese with parsley and oregano, Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
In a 13 x 9-inch oblong pan, layer ingredients, starting and ending with the sauce.

title: tortellini alfredo
directions: Cook tortellini as directed on package.
Saute mushrooms in butter.
Add ham.
Cook 1 minute.
Reserve liquid.
Remove ham and mushrooms.
Make Alfredo Sauce with reserved liquid, half and half and Parmesan cheese.
Add peas, ham and mushrooms.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add tortellini.
Blend thoroughly.
Serve.

title: tomato relish
directions: Cut up fine.
Mix with 2 cups of salt.
Hang in large cloth bag to drip.
(I use a pillow case.)
Let drip 24 hours.

title: pretzel fruit salad
directions: Mix pretzels, 1/4 cup sugar and butter.
Press into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool crust.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix sugar, salt and flour. Cut in Crisco. Mix egg, vinegar and water. Add to flour mixture.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer the lettuce, mayonnaise (salad dressing), sugar, peas, onion and cheese.
Refrigerate for 10 hours.
Before serving, layer bacon and eggs.

title: holiday punch
directions: Reconstitute cranberry juice and lemonade per directions on cans.
Add orange juice concentrate.
Just before serving, add the club soda.
Mix and serve chilled.
Makes 25 to 30 (4 ounce) servings.

title: hot chili bean and corn salad
directions: Combine beans, corn, celery and picante sauce. Set out at room temperature 1 hour before serving. To serve immediately, defrost corn in microwave. Cook on High for half of recommended cooking time or cook in boiling water according to package directions. Drain and cool slightly before adding to salad. Garnish with fresh cilantro leaves, if desired.

title: scrambled eggs
directions: Crack two hard eggs in a cup or pot.
Put a little bit of milk in the same cup or pot with the two cracked eggs.
Melt butter in another big pot.
Pour eggs in. While cooking, add as much salt as you want.
When cooked enough, take out.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream first three ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients to creamed mixture.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 8 x 8 inch pan.
Mix flour, sugar and milk together.
Pour batter into buttered pan.
Pour fruit, with a little juice, on top.
Bake at 350 degrees until done (25-30 minutes).
Serve with ice cream.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together mayo, sugar and 2 tablespoons vinegar to dissolve sugar.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Stir and pour over broccoli, onions and sunflower seeds.
Top with bacon.

title: peach pie
directions: Line pie pan with crust and fill with sliced peaches.
Sprinkle cinnamon over peaches.
Beat eggs well, add sugar, flour and shortening.
Pour over peaches.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 325° for 40 minutes.
A crust will form over top of pie.

title: texas caviar
directions: Combine all ingredients together.

title: chicken and wild rice
directions: Cook wild rice mix in chicken broth.
Combine with all remaining ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake 50 minutes at 350°.
Serves 10.

title: lasagne florentine
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a medium bowl, combine Ricotta cheese, egg, Parmesan cheese and garlic powder.
Spread 1/3 of spaghetti sauce over bottom of a baking dish.
Cover with 3 uncooked noodles.
Top with half Ricotta cheese mixture and then sprinkle with 1 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat steps until all noodles are used.
Cover with foil and bake 45 to 50 minutes or until noodles are tender.

title: fried corn
directions: Cook bacon in skillet until crisp; drain reserving 2 tablespoons bacon drippings.
Add corn, 1 1/2 cups water, sugar and salt to bacon drippings in skillet.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer, covered, for 20 to 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Combine cornstarch and 1 tablespoon water in bowl; mix well.
Stir into corn mixture.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Pour into serving bowl.
Crumble bacon over top.

title: stir-fry low-fat chicken
directions: Cut up chicken; simmer in soy sauce or olive oil until semi-done.
Cut up carrots and put in chicken (add 1 chicken cube dissolved in 3/4 cup of water).
Add broccoli, cauliflower and green onions (optional).
Simmer until tender.
Cook rice and put into mixture; add soy sauce as needed.

title: italian squash
directions: Saute garlic clove, onion and pepper together in olive oil. Add cooked, cubed squash, tomatoes, oregano, basil and salt and pepper.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Put apples in a baking pan.
Pour mixture over apples.
Melt butter, then pour over apples. Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Combine dissolved jello with pie filling and crushed pineapple.
When almost set, stir in whipping cream and nuts.

title: quick and easy pork chop casserole
directions: Cut potatoes into 1/8-inch rounds and layer in casserole dish or baking pan which has been greased.
Alternate potatoes and chopped onion in layers and season each layer.
Top last layer with pork chops and pour cream of mushroom soup over entire casserole.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are cooked through.

title: bitter and sweet salad
directions: Arrange greens in a shallow bowl.
Top with olives, onions, Prosciutto and cheese.
In a saucepan, roast garlic in the olive oil over a low heat.
Add sugar, then vinegars.
Pour over the salad while still warm.

title: cheese boxes
directions: Beat the first 4 ingredients until smooth.
Spread filling across each slice of bread, then stack 4 slices on top of one another.
Cut off crusts.
Cut each in fourths.
Ice the sides of each square.
Freeze.
Bake, frozen, in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour 2 cups boiling water over 100% Bran.
Set aside.
Cream the shortening, sugar and eggs. Sift and add flour, soda and salt into egg mixture. Add cooled Bran mixture.
Stir in buttermilk and All-Bran. Bake in greased muffin tins at 400° about 20 to 22 minutes.
Keep batter in refrigerator. Do not stir batter when you take some out! Makes 6 dozen muffins.

title: nachos
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add taco seasoning, refried beans and chili. Crush chips and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put meat on top and cover with cheese.
Bake at 350°
until cheese melts.

title: zucchini nut loaf
directions: In mixing bowl, stir together flour, cinnamon, baking powder, salt, nutmeg and baking soda; set aside.
In a mixing bowl, beat together sugar, shredded zucchini and egg.
Add oil and lemon peel; mix well.
Stir flour mixture into zucchini mixture.
Gently fold in chopped nuts.
Turn batter into a greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool thoroughly on a rack.
Wrap and store overnight before slicing.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: instant cheese pie
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, butter and sugar together.
Press into a 9-inch pie pan.
Chill.
Pour sour cream and cold milk into a mixing bowl.
Add the cream cheese and instant pudding.
Beat with electric mixer for 1 minute or until smooth.
Pour cheese mixture into the prepared pie crust.
Chill until set.
Garnish with a thin "frosting" of sour cream, if desired.

title: mexican hominy and chili(from the files of adness williams crutchfield)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven or until it bubbles.

title: girl scout yum yums
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over low heat.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Let cool.
Add crumbs, nuts and marshmallows.
Mix well.
Spread in buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Chill several hours. Yum! Yum!

title: self-rising flour
directions: Combine 1 cup regular flour, less 2 teaspoons.
Add baking powder and salt.

title: wassail(a good christmas or new year's drink.)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Simmer at least 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all together and bake in greased pan (9 x 5-inch) or 12-cup muffin pan at 425° until golden brown, about 25 minutes.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Mix beef, noodles and onion.
Mix soup and milk; pour over noodles, etc.
Pour into pan and spread with grated cheese.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: congo squares
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Add oil, eggs, chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 325° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: squash fritters
directions: Mix all
ingredients and drop by spoonful into hot oil, enough oil
to
cover
bottom
of	pan good.
Fry until golden brown on both sides.

title: fudgy bonbons
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
In medium saucepan, combine chocolate chips and butter.
Cook and stir over very low heat until melted and smooth.
Add Eagle Brand milk; mix well.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In medium bowl, combine flour, nuts, chocolate mixture and vanilla; mix well.
Shape 1 tablespoon of dough around each candy hug, covering completely.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes.
Cookies will be soft and shiny.
Remove; cool.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Combine in large bowl.
Mix until well blended.
Batter may be a little lumpy.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Pour mixture into loaf pans evenly and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Start heating oven to 375°.
Sift flour with baking powder. Mix margarine with cheese.
Add granulated sugar and mix thoroughly.
Add egg, lemon rind and 1 tablespoon juice; mix well. Mix in flour mixture.
Refrigerate 1/2 hour.
Force dough through ribbon disk of cookie press onto ungreased cold cookie sheet (or drop by teaspoon).
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden.
Mix confectioners sugar with 2 tablespoons lemon juice.
When cookies are cool, dip one end of each in frosting, then pecans.

title: dilly carrot dip
directions: Place ingredients in food processor, cover and process with metal blade until smooth.
Serve with assorted crackers and vegetable dippers.
Or cover and store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Stir before serving.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: aunt sally sampson's baked beans
directions: Rinse can out with about a cup or a little more of water and add to bean mixture.
Bake in 375° oven for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: yummy cheese ball
directions: Mix cheeses, garlic salt and onion together.
Fold in pimentos. Chill until stiff.
Roll into ball and roll in chopped pecans, if desired.
Ball can be rolled in chopped parsley or chives, also.

title: three minute fudge
directions: Mix milk, sugar and salt in 2-quart saucepan.
Heat to boiling over low heat.
Boil and stir 3 minutes or until candy thermometer reads 225°.
Remove from heat, add marshmallows, chocolate chips, vanilla and nuts, stirring until marshmallows and chocolate are melted.
Pour into buttered square pan (9 x 9 x 2-inch). Refrigerate until firm. Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: bread sticks
directions: Cut into thirds, 6 slices.
Melt butter.
Brush on bread. Sprinkle with garlic, sesame seed and caraway seed.
Bake 1 hour at 250°.

title: crazy cake(easy!)
directions: Mix sugar, flour, baking soda, cocoa and salt.
Add vinegar, oil, water and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into a 9 x 12-inch greased baking pan.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients with a fork until well mixed.
Cut tops off peppers and remove seeds.
Fill with chopped meat mixture (do not pack into peppers).
Place side by side in large Dutch oven pot.
Mix the 2 cans of soup together.
Pour tomato soup over peppers.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.

title: salsa verde
directions: In food processor or blender, combine all ingredients; process to smooth puree.
In a 12-inch nonstick skillet over medium heat, heat 1 tablespoon vegetable oil (preferably canola).
Add tomato mixture and granulated sugar.
Cook about 4 minutes, stirring frequently, until sauce is slightly thickened.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: quick and easy dip
directions: Mix together in bowl and put back into sour cream container until serving time.
Will keep for 2 weeks.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together Crisco, butter and the two sugars.
Add egg and vanilla.
Sift together and add dry ingredients.
Add the chocolate chips and nuts and bake at 350° just until done.

title: cherry fruit salad
directions: Mix condensed milk and lemon juice in large bowl.
Add the cherry pie filling and pineapple; mix well.
Stir in the vanilla. Add Cool Whip and pecans.
Chill in refrigerator at least 1 hour before serving.

title: bean dip el grande
directions: In a large 2-inch deep serving dish, place refried beans evenly on bottom.
Spread 1/2 package taco seasoning over beans as well as a dash of Tabasco sauce.
Spread salsa evenly over beans, then sprinkle half of the olives.
Spread sour cream over the olives and then spread guacamole dip.
Layer lettuce over the guacamole and then sprinkle tomato and olives.
Sprinkle cheese on last.
Serve fresh or chilled.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place bread crumbs in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine cheese, eggs, milk and soup.
Pour over bread crumbs.
Sprinkle sausage over top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine tomato sauce, brown sugar, vinegar and mustard in a small bowl.
Set aside.
Combine egg, onion, cracker crumbs, ground beef, salt and pepper in a mixing bowl.
Add 1/2 cup of the tomato mixture and blend thoroughly.
Shape into an oval loaf and place in an oblong baking dish.
Make a depression in top of loaf. Pour remaining tomato sauce over top of meat.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix condensed milk, egg yolks and lemon juice and pulp together until it begins to thicken.
Pour into pie crust and top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for at least 3 to 4 hours so that it will set up.

title: boiled custard
directions: Into double boiler, put the milk to get hot (not boil).
Beat the eggs and add sugar and mix well.
Pour a small portion of hot milk into egg mixture, then add back into milk in double boiler, stirring until thickened.
Add vanilla flavoring.
Set aside to cool the custard before serving.

title: squash with shredded almonds
directions: Boil squash in salted water until cooked but not too soft. Fry minced onion in butter until slightly yellow.
Add to squash and season with salt and pepper; add a dash of oregano.
Heat sour cream.
Rub flour with small amount of the cream.
Stir into the whole, a little at a time.
Add almonds; stir until sauce thickens.
Pour over squash and mix well.
We put the mixture in a casserole.
Turn it into the oven for further heating and browning and add parsley or chives just before serving.

title: buttermilk rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Let set 5 minutes.
Add oil.
Add dry ingredients.
Add milk; mix.
Knead.
Place in a greased bowl. Cover and refrigerate.
Pinch into biscuits and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: almond sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in the order they appear.
Refrigerate in a covered bowl for at least 2 hours.
Roll out to 1/2 inch thick. Cut into desired shapes and bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: kincaid mcclellan's applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter
and
sugar; beat in eggs.
Add flour with spices sifted together, alternately with applesauce, with soda stirred in.
Add raisins and put in 9 x 9-inch pan and bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
May add 1/2 cup nuts.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Combine and serve with Poppy Seed Dressing.

title: ultimate chocolate cake
directions: Place all ingredients except chips in bowl.
Beat at low speed to moisten.
Beat at medium speed until creamy.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Grease tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix pineapple juice (from drained pineapple), flour, sugar and eggs and cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add butter. Let cool, then add pineapple, nuts and marshmallows.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine flour, salt and soda in bowl. In large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugars.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add slowly to flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips. Drop by teaspoon on greased baking sheet and bake for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken breasts and dressing
directions: Mix soup and sour cream together and then spread over the cut up chicken in Pyrex baking dish or cake pan.
Mix Pepperidge Farm dressing mix with more bread crumbs, celery, onion and eggs.
If needed, add more water.
Spread dressing over soup/sour cream mixture.
Dot with butter or oleo.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar; add molasses and egg.
Blend well.
Sift all dry ingredients together; add to creamed mixture. Mix well.
Roll into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place 2 1/2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly.
Press almond into each.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: calico beans
directions: Go out in the "cuntree" or on the roadside or fencerow and pick yourself some poke.
Be sure to git small tender leaves and don't git snake bit.
Bring 'em home an' throw 'em in a pot an' boil 'em up good.
Then scramble you up some fresh aggs an' mix 'em with the fresh poke an' add a tastin' of some salt an' you got yo'self some poke salad.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut beef into thin strips.
Combine soy sauce, garlic and ginger.
Add beef.
Toss and set aside.
(May marinate beef in refrigerator for 2 hours.)
Heat oil in a large pan or wok.
Add beef; cook until browned.
Cover and simmer on low for 30 to 40 minutes.
Turn heat up and add cut up vegetables.
Cook about 10 minutes or until tender crisp.
Mix cornstarch with water.
Stir. Add to meat and vegetables.
Stir and cook until thickened.
Add tomatoes and sugar.
Heat through.

title: new potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes with skins on.
When cool, slice 1/4-inch thick and layer half of potatoes in a large 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish. Sprinkle with seasonings.
Cover with half the bacon and half the cheese.
Repeat with potatoes, seasonings, bacon and cheese. Dribble melted butter over all. Heat at 325° until hot (about 25 to 30 minutes).
If done ahead of time, leave off butter until right before it goes into the oven.
Good with hamburgers, steaks, etc.

title: carrot souffle
directions: Pare and cook carrots until tender; drain well.
Mash carrots. Combine all ingredients and beat until smooth.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: baked mushroom casserole
directions: Oil bottom of 1 large baking pan.
Mix mushrooms, bread crumbs, crackers and roasted peppers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, mixing occasionally to firm and brown texture.
Top with grated cheese last 10 minutes until done.
Mix in Worcestershire sauce.
Enjoy--hot!!
Serves 6.

title: outside-in burgers
directions: Shape beef into 16 (1/4-inch thick) patties.
For filling, combine cheese and catsup or mustard.
Place about 2 tablespoons filling on each of 8 patties. Top with remaining patties. Press edges. Chill 3 hours. Grill, turning once.
Serve with lettuce and tomatoes.

title: fruit ambrosia
directions: Cut up oranges.
Slice bananas, apples and pineapple. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Chill.
Dress up with coconut, pecans or cherries before serving.

title: chocolate pie
directions: In a heavy skillet, combine sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add 2 egg yolks and 1 cup milk, stirring until blended.
Add remaining milk and salt.
Cook over low to medium heat until mixture is thick. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Pour into ready baked pie crust. Beat the 2 egg whites plus two tablespoons of cold water until thick.
Add one tablespoon sugar while beating.
Pour over chocolate pie and place in oven at 350° until meringue browns.

title: beans mexicana
directions: Saute beef (crumbled), onions and pepper.
Add beans, corn, chilies and seasoning.
Simmer a few minutes or bake in medium oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: chicken and potatoes
directions: Brown chicken pieces in frypan.
After browning, place in baking pan.
Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Place potatoes and onions in pan.
In saucepan, stew tomatoes with green pepper, celery, chicken stock and seasonings.
(Simmer until vegetables are tender.)
Pour over chicken, onions and potatoes.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 25 minutes longer, basting with sauce.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate macaroon pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375.
Place a circle of parchment paper on a pizza pan.
Prepare brownie mix according to package directions. Pour brownie mix on parchment paper.
Bake 15-18 minutes or until brownie is set.

title: corn chowder
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large kettle and heat very slow. Stir often.
Do not add salt.
It serves 6 or more people.

title: cherry chewbilees
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with butter-flavored Crisco and set aside.
Chop 1/2 cup nuts coarsely for topping and set aside.
Chop remaining 1/2 cup finely.
For crust, combine flour and brown sugar.
Cut in Crisco until fine crumbs form.
Add 1/2 cup finely chopped nuts and coconut.
Mix well.
Remove 1/2 cup and set aside.
Press remaining crumbs into bottom of pan.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes until edges are lightly browned.

title: potato lefsa
directions: Mix potatoes, lard and salt together and chill thoroughly.

title: cream puff shells
directions: Put water, salt and butter in saucepan; heat to boiling.
Add flour; stir vigorously until mixture no longer sticks to sides of pan.
Cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat after each egg.
On greased baking sheet, drop mixture by tablespoon leaving 2 inches between puffs.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
Reduce to 325° and bake 20 minutes more.
Cool puffs; cut off tops and fill with pudding, then replace tops.

title: skors cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed.
While still hot, poke holes in cake with a wooden spoon handle.
Pour Eagle Brand milk and ice cream topping over cake.
Let cool in refrigerator, then cover with Cool Whip and crushed candy bars.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Pour into bowl the pumpkin, spices, pudding mix (right out of box) and cream cheese.
Mix well and pour into baked pie shells. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Top with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: In a medium bowl, dissolve the Jell-O in boiling water.
Allow to cool.
Peel and shred the apples.
Add to Jell-O along with pecans and cranberry sauce. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch glass pan. Refrigerate until firm.
Blend together Cool Whip, cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth.
Add vanilla and pineapple. Spread evenly over Jell-O mixture. Refrigerate overnight.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown
beef
and onion in oil.
Add garlic, salt, tomatoes and
chili
powder.
Break up spaghetti.
Add to mixture along with
water.
Put in casserole dish and top with cheese. Bake covered for 35 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake another 15 minutes.

title: dirt dessert #1
directions: You will need 9 or 10-inch plastic potting plant container.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream butter till soft, add sugar and cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Mix together flour, soda, baking powder and salt;
add to first mixture.
Alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour half of batter into lightly greased 13 x 9 inch pan. cover batter with half filling/topping mixture.
Add remaining batter and other half of filling.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend cheese and seasoning salt and remaining ingredients. Chill 4 to 6 hours.

title: three onion relish
directions: Toss onions with salt in large bowl.
Transfer to colander in sink and let sit 30 minutes.
Rinse in cold water and squeeze dry. Transfer to nonaluminum bowl.
Add vinegar, sugar, peel and thyme.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: microwave mississippi mud
directions: Microwave butter and cocoa in 2 1/2-quart, glass casserole at High power for 2 minutes.
Stir in sugar.
Add eggs and beat well. Blend in flour, salt, vanilla and nuts.

title: italian love cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch pan. In separate bowl, mix well Ricotta cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Spoon cheese mixture on top of unbaked cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bruschetta al fresca
directions: In medium bowl, gently mix together first 5 ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour to allow flavors to blend.
Spread baguette slices with garlic spread; broil until lightly brown and bubbly, about 3 to 4 minutes.
Top each slice with 1 tablespoon tomato mixture and garnish with cheese.

title: nut and herb popcorn
directions: About 30 minutes before serving or early in day:
Prepare popcorn as label directs.
(You will have about 16 cups popped corn, depending on brand used.) In large roasting pan or bowl, mix olive oil, rosemary, thyme, salt and pepper.
Add popcorn and cashews; toss to coat well.
Store popcorn mixture in tightly covered containers.
Makes about 18 cups.

title: fruit salad
directions: Dice pears; add pineapple and peach filling.
About 1 hour before serving, slice the bananas and some maraschino cherries and carefully fold in.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cover apples with sugar in a bowl; let stand for 20 minutes. Add egg, flour, baking soda, salt, oil and spices; mix well.
Add nuts.
Bake in a 6 x 10 x 2-inch glass bread pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
(If aluminum pan is used, add another 5 minutes.)
Can be doubled.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Put pecans and coconut in bottom.
Mix cake mix according to directions.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and margarine.
Drop by spoonfuls on top of mix.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: applesauce-raisin bread
directions: Place all dry ingredients in large bowl.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Combine eggs, applesauce and oil.
Add to dry ingredients and stir just until blended.
Divide batter into 4 greased mini loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Test for doneness. Makes 4 mini loaves.

title: chocolate mousse pie
directions: Prepare Oreo cookie crust (which is best) by mixing 1 1/2 cups crumbled Oreo cookies with 1/3 cup melted margarine.
Press in pie pan.
Or use 1 (8-inch) graham cracker crust.

title: chinese food(chicken)
directions: Brown chicken breast pieces in 3 tablespoons oil. Brown onions and peppers.
Cook frozen vegetables mildly.
Add bamboo shoots and water chestnuts.
Heat chicken broth and add cornstarch; mix together.
Salt, pepper, garlic and soy sauce to taste.

title: artichoke squares
directions: Saute onion and garlic in a little butter until limp.
Add eggs, bread crumbs and seasonings.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch greased pan and bake at 350° until set, or about 30 minutes.
Cut in small squares.

title: chicken with cranberries
directions: Coat chicken pieces in flour, brown in oil and butter and set aside.
In a saucepan combine rest of ingredients, bringing to a boil.
Pour over chicken and cook for 35 to 40 minutes and serve. Rice goes well.

title: fiesta (party) chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Combine the chicken broth and salsa. Pour in casserole dish.
Add uncooked rice.
Stir in onion, celery and pepper.
Place uncooked chicken breast halves on top of the rice and salsa mixture.
Cover with foil and bake 30 minutes. Uncover and sprinkle chicken with Cheddar cheese.
Cover and bake an additional 30 minutes, until all liquid is absorbed and cheese has melted.
Let rest 10 minutes before serving.

title: baked chili
directions: Place beef in skillet, cook until it loses its color.
Combine tomato soup with meat, then add other ingredients.
Place in casserole dish and bake in 325° oven for about two hours.

title: texas chili
directions: Cook the ground beef, bell pepper and onion.
Drain off fat. In large pot add beans, soup and milk.
Mix in the ground beef, pepper and onion.
Cook over medium-low heat for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, white sugar and brown sugar.
Add and blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add peanut butter.
Sift together flour, soda and salt and blend in.
Form into small balls; place on cookie sheet and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hawaiian cake topping
directions: Blend cream cheese, pudding and milk.
Spread on top of sheet cake.
Spread crushed pineapple over the top.
Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut and nuts.

title: strawberry nut cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together then add the rest of the ingredients.
Beat with mixer until there is no more lumps.
Pour into a greased pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spiced walnuts
directions: Beat egg white and water until frothy.
Toss nuts in egg white until coated.
Mix together sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt. Cover nuts with dry mixture.
Spread into buttered pan.
Toast in oven at 300° for 1/2 hour, turning every 10 minutes.

title: south of border dip(spicy)
directions: Brown meat; drain and put into crock-pot.
Add sauce, paste, chopped chilies and peppers.
Dice up cheese and add to other ingredients.
Cook 3 to 4 hours on medium heat.
Stir often so cheese will melt.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Great for parties. Verrry spicy.

title: chewy bread
directions: Melt oleo or have at room temperature, add sugar; beat well. Add eggs, one at a time, add flour, vanilla and pecans.
Grease 2 (9 x 13-inch) cookie sheets, place 1/2 dough on each sheet. Spread dough (will be real thin).
Bake at 300° for 15 to 17 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash, onion and 1/4 stick butter till tender.
Drain. Add 1/4 stick butter, egg and handful of crushed Ritz crackers. Add milk to consistency of mashed potatoes.
Pour into greased casserole dish.

title: grace's pineapple chiffon pie
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and pineapple.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatin.
Let cool while whipping evaporated milk until it is thick.
Mix whipped milk with filling and pour into a cooked pie crust.
Chill.

title: presto pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Rinse with cold water and drain.
Combine pasta and remaining ingredients; toss well.
Serve immediately or, if desired, chill.

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: In mixing bowl, cream shortening and sugar. Add boiling water; stir until dissolved. Add yeast mixture. Add egg that has been slightly beaten, flour and salt. Refrigerate overnight. Next morning, work down and cut like biscuits.
Let rise 3 or 4 hours and bake in a 400° oven.

title: ambrosia fruit dip
directions: Carve balls from your favorite melon and serve with fancy toothpicks to accompany this tasty dip.
This dip can also be served as a topping for any fruit salad.

title: caramel corn
directions: Bring to boil the first 4 ingredients, then boil 2 minutes. Stir in soda.
Pour over popcorn in brown bag.
Cook in microwave in bag on High for 3 1/2 minutes.
Shake bag every 30 seconds.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Drop into hot oil and fry approximately 4 minutes on each side.
(You can also grate carrots and/or zucchini into mixture.)

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease bottom of three 4 1/2 x 8 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Cream shortening and sugar in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, zucchini and water; mix well.
Add dry ingredients gradually, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla and raisins.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pans for 5 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool completely.
Store, wrapped in plastic wrap, in refrigerator for up to 10 days.
Yields 30 slices.

title: 7 up cake
directions: Mix well and bake at 325.

title: southern delight
directions: Mix flour, butter & nuts, press in bottom of a 9 X 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, cool.	Mix whipped cream, powdered sugar & cream cheese, spread over crust.
Arrange a layer of sliced bananas on top of that.
Mix pudding mixes with milk until thick.
Spread over the last layer.
Cover with more whipped cream.
Sprinkle top with a few more ground nuts if desired. Delicious!

title: chili
directions: Cook onion in small amount of oil for 5 minutes.
Crumble hamburger and brown.
Add tomato paste, kidney beans, juice and seasonings.
Add 1/2 can water.
Cook at least one hour, stirring often.
Chili should be very thick.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: homemade vanilla no cook ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.

Add the cream, half and half, vanilla, salt and milk (enough to fill the container 2/3 full). If you wish, you may add 2 cups of your favorite sweetened fruit, crushed after you have placed the creams and flavorings in freezer container.
Add enough milk to bring up to level as given above. Freeze in dasher-type freezer according to directions.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: three flavor pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat in, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk that has flavoring in it.

title: italian shell bake
directions: Brown ground beef in large skillet.
Add onion and saute until tender.
Pour off excess fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, garlic salt, oregano and pepper; simmer.
While this simmers, cook medium shells according to package; drain well.
Combine Ricotta, 1 1/2 cups Mozzarella and chopped parsley; mix well.
Combine shells with meat sauce.
Place 1/2 of the mixture into a buttered pan. Spread cheese filling evenly over shells.
Do again with shells and meat mixture; spread cheese mixture.
Sprinkle Mozzarella. Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: seafoam candy
directions: Combine sugar, water and Karo; cook until mixture makes a firm ball when tested in cool water.
Pour slowly over well beaten egg whites.
Beat until it begins to cream; then add nuts and vanilla. When candy has creamed enough to hold shape drop from a spoon onto buttered plates.

title: turkey and wild rice
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir well.
Spoon into a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Uncover and bake an additional 5 to 10 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine 1 tablespoon flour and salt; dredge meat in mixture. Heat pan.
Add 2 tablespoons butter.
When melted, add beef and brown quickly on all sides.
Add mushrooms, onion and garlic; cook for 3 to 4 minutes, until onion is tender.
Remove meat and mushrooms to platter.
Add 2 tablespoons butter to pan drippings. When melted, blend in 3 tablespoons flour.
Add tomato paste. Slowly pour in cold meat stock.
Cook and stir until thickened. Return browned meat and mushrooms to pan.
Stir in sour cream and sherry; heat briefly.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from cocktail and tidbits.
Put in separate bowls. In bowl with juice, add pudding and Tang. Whip together and pour over cocktail, bananas and tidbits.
Mix well.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix together the softened cream cheese and sugar well.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Add Cool Whip and chocolate chips. Pour into pie crust and freeze for 2 hours.

title: australian damper "out-back" bread
directions: Beat butter and sugar until creamy; add egg and beat again. Then, add milk alternately with flour (to which salt, cream of tartar and soda have been added).
Turn out on a well-floured board.
Knead and shape into 2 pones and place on well-greased baking pans.
Brush tops with melted butter.
Bake at 350° until top is browned.

title: springtime tea cakes
directions: Grease bottom of 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan; line with waxed paper and grease paper.
Cream butter until soft in large bowl; add sugar gradually, beating after each addition until mixture is fluffy.
Stir in vanilla.
Measure cake flour, baking powder and salt into sifter.
Sift and add dry ingredients alternately with milk, blending until smooth after each addition.

title: molasses whole wheat bread
directions: Mix together sugar, whole wheat flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Combine milk, water and molasses.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
Add walnuts.
Pour into 9 1/4 x 5 1/4 x 2 1/2-inch greased loaf pan.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Bake in 350°
oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Remove from pan. Cool.
Bread will slice in nice thin slices if stored overnight.

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: Combine cake mix, fruit cocktail with juice, 1 cup of the coconut and the eggs in a large bowl; blend.
Then beat at medium speed 2 minutes.

title: creamy enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add chopped pepper and onion to beef and cook until vegetables are tender.
Drain grease from meat and add Ro-Tel green chilies and tomato sauce.
Simmer.
Cut Velveeta cheese into chunks and melt with the Pet milk.
Roll the beef mixture in tortillas and secure with toothpick.
Pour cheese mixture over enchiladas and bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: bean burritos
directions: The night before, put 2 cups beans and 6 cups water in crock-pot.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Simmer sugar and butter for about 5 minutes.
Add other ingredients.
Stir until thickens.
I cook in microwave.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue.

title: homemade fudge
directions: Bring sugar, margarine and Pet milk to a boil; boil for 8 minutes.
Add in the vanilla, marshmallows, chips and nuts.
Pour into a well-greased pan and chill.

title: chile rellenos casserole
directions: Split whole chiles lengthwise and remove seeds under cold water.
Lay chiles flat in bottom of pan, sprayed with Pam.
Mix cheeses.
Top chiles with a layer until chiles and cheese are used.
Beat together the eggs, dry mustard and evaporated milk. Pour over cheese and chili mixture.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch dish at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until knife inserted comes out clean. Serve with salsa.
Serves 8.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Cut biscuits in half.
Put half in round cake pan.
Melt butter.
Add brown sugar and cinnamon.
Stir until sugar is dissolved; add nuts.
Spoon on biscuits; put other half on top. Spoon topping on.
Bake at 375° for 13 to 15 minutes.

title: camp meeting roast(large quantity recipe)
directions: If roasts are very big, cut in half. Sprinkle roast with salt, pepper, and garlic salt (or powder). Place roast in warmers and fill warmers about one third full of water. Cook at 350° between 5 and 6 hours, or until roast are tender. Remove roast and stir in gravy mix; stir in mushroom soup. If gravy appears too thick, add more hot water. Put roast back in gravy and cook about 1 more hour at 350°.

title: zucchini walnut bread
directions: Beat eggs and zucchini in blender, add sugar, oil and dry ingredients alternately.
Stir in raisins, nuts and vanilla.
Turn into 3 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: In a medium sized saucepan combine butter, corn syrup, brown sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil; boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and immediately add baking soda.
Stir well.
Using a large microwave-safe bowl, combine popcorn and hot caramel syrup. Try to cover as much of the popcorn as possible.
Set microwave on Full power (High); "zap" for 45 seconds.
Stir to coat popcorn. Repeat 45 seconds "zapping" and again stir to coat.
The third time, "zap" for 30 seconds.
Let cool and break up large chunks. Make two batches because the first batch will be gone in no time.

title: cracker salad
directions: Crush crackers and put in large mixing bowl. Add all ingredients and mix well. This salad is better if covered and chilled for a couple hours before serving. Will keep for several days in refrigerator.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Melt cheese and milk over low heat.
Add pimentos, vinegar, sugar and egg.
Cook 15-20 minutes. Add mayonnaise.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Mix together popcorn, peanuts and M&M's.
Melt marshmallows, butter and oil.
Pour over popcorn mixture.
Press into greased angel food pan; cool. Turn out.

title: low-fat pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray an 8 x 8 x 2-inch square pan with cooking spray.
